748	995	listening_tests	ee6c4d93-ba0a-4fcf-90f9-29a19f9a82ff	{"id":"ee6c4d93-ba0a-4fcf-90f9-29a19f9a82ff","title":"Sports Complex Grounds Tour","slug":"sports-complex-grounds-tour","description":"An outdoor map of a sports complex showing a main entrance at the south, a central path running north to south through the grounds, a north gate at the top, and eight labelled areas or buildings distributed across the site.","accent":"British English","duration_seconds":null,"question_count":6,"is_free":true,"instruction_text":"Label the map below. Write the correct letter, A-H, next to Questions 1-6.","transcript":"Welcome to the Northfield Sports Complex. I am the facilities coordinator, and I am going to take you through the layout of the grounds so you know exactly where everything is.\\n\\nAs you come through the Main Entrance at the south end, you will notice two areas on either side of you. On your left, just inside the entrance, is where you can get changed before your session. On the right as you walk in, there used to be a reception office, but that has been relocated to the main building near the centre of the site. What you now find on the right, just inside the entrance, is the car park office, where staff manage vehicle access and issue permits.\\n\\nIf you continue north along the Central Path and look to your left roughly halfway along, you will come across the area for hiring equipment. This is a popular stop for visitors who have not brought their own kit. Directly opposite, on the right side of the path at the same point, is a maintenance block used by the groundskeeping team. This area is not open to the public.\\n\\nFurther along on the left-hand side, before you reach the North Gate, is the spectator seating area. This looks out over the main activity zone. On the opposite side of the grounds at mid-level, to the right, is a storage facility. Please note that access to the storage facility is restricted to authorised personnel only, so visitors should not attempt to enter.\\n\\nNow, up near the North Gate itself, there are two further areas. On the far left as you face the gate is where you can get refreshments. There were plans to move this to the centre of the complex, but in the end it remained in the top-left corner. On the far right, just before the North Gate, is where you will find the first aid point, which is staffed during all opening hours.","prosody_script":null,"date_created":"2026-06-18T14:54:33.593Z","date_updated":"2026-06-18T14:54:33.593Z","status":"published","metadata":{"schema_version":"visual_labelling_listening_v1","topic":"Sports Complex Grounds","speaker_role":"Facilities Coordinator","image_generation_prompt":"Create a clean, simple outdoor map of a sports complex. The map is oriented with south at the bottom and north at the top. Draw a clearly labelled 'Main Entrance' at the bottom centre. Draw a straight vertical path labelled 'Central Path' running from the Main Entrance at the bottom to a 'North Gate' at the top centre. All eight labelled areas must appear as plain, neutral rectangles or blocks only — no icons, no signs, no pictograms, no furniture, no equipment, no sports-related objects, no symbols, and no text that reveals their function. Place letter labels as follows: Label A is a neutral block in the lower-left area just inside the Main Entrance, to the left of the Central Path. Label B is a neutral block in the lower-right area just inside the Main Entrance, to the right of the Central Path. Label C is a neutral block on the left side of the map at mid-level. Label D is a neutral block on the right side of the map at mid-level. Label E is a neutral block at the top-left corner near the North Gate. Label F is a neutral block at the top-right corner near the North Gate. Label G is a neutral block on the left side of the Central Path just below mid-level. Label H is a neutral block on the right side of the Central Path at mid-level, directly opposite Label G. Only the fixed orientation landmarks — Main Entrance, Central Path, and North Gate — may have visible text. All labelled blocks must be visually identical and show only their letter. Do not add decorative clutter, sports courts, fields, trees, benches, or any other objects that could help learners identify the function of any labelled area.","difficulty_notes":{"word_count":319,"visible_label_count":8,"question_count":6,"distractor_label_count":2,"why_this_level":"B2 is appropriate because the transcript contains 319 words, 8 visible labels, 6 questions, and 2 distractor labels. The transcript uses changed location information (the reception office has moved), negation and restriction language (not open to the public, access restricted), and multi-step spatial directions. Distractors include a relocated reception office, a maintenance block opposite the equipment hire area, and a storage facility on the right at mid-level.","distractors":["The reception office is mentioned as a former use of the lower-right area, but the correct answer for that location is now the car park office.","The maintenance block at mid-level right is described as not open to the public — label H is the distractor for that position.","The storage facility on the right at mid-level is mentioned but is not a question target — label D is the distractor for that position. The plans to move the refreshments area to the centre are introduced and then negated."],"key_phrases":["just inside the entrance","used to be a reception office, but that has been relocated","on the left roughly halfway along","directly opposite","not open to the public","before you reach the North Gate","on the far left as you face the gate","on the far right, just before the North Gate"],"visual_fairness_check":{"can_learners_guess_answers_from_image_alone":false,"anti_leak_checked":true,"notes":"All eight labelled areas appear as plain neutral blocks with no icons, signs, furniture, equipment, or symbols. Only the fixed orientation landmarks — Main Entrance, Central Path, and North Gate — have visible text. No correct answer name or distractor function is revealed visually."}}},"questions_public_json":{"groups":[{"id":"g1","type":"map_labelling","title":"Questions 1-6","instruction":"Label the map below. Write the correct letter, A-H, next to Questions 1-6.","question_range":{"from":1,"to":6},"media":{"image":{"type":"image","field":"image_file"},"audio":{"type":"audio","field":"audio_file"}},"options":{"type":"letters","values":["A","B","C","D","E","F","G","H"]},"questions":[{"id":"q1","number":1,"text":"Changing Rooms","input_type":"select","score":1},{"id":"q2","number":2,"text":"Car Park Office","input_type":"select","score":1},{"id":"q3","number":3,"text":"Equipment Hire","input_type":"select","score":1},{"id":"q4","number":4,"text":"Spectator Seating","input_type":"select","score":1},{"id":"q5","number":5,"text":"Outdoor Cafe","input_type":"select","score":1},{"id":"q6","number":6,"text":"First Aid Point","input_type":"select","score":1}]}]},"questions_answer_json":[{"id":"q1","correct_answer":"A","acceptable_answers":["A"],"score":1,"explanation":"The changing rooms are located in the lower-left area, just inside the Main Entrance on the left-hand side, which corresponds to label A.","transcript_evidence":"On your left, just inside the entrance, is where you can get changed before your session."},{"id":"q2","correct_answer":"B","acceptable_answers":["B"],"score":1,"explanation":"The car park office is in the lower-right area, just inside the Main Entrance on the right-hand side, which corresponds to label B. The transcript explains the previous use (reception office) has moved and that the car park office is now in that position.","transcript_evidence":"What you now find on the right, just inside the entrance, is the car park office, where staff manage vehicle access and issue permits."},{"id":"q3","correct_answer":"G","acceptable_answers":["G"],"score":1,"explanation":"The equipment hire area is on the left side of the Central Path roughly halfway along the path, which corresponds to label G.","transcript_evidence":"If you continue north along the Central Path and look to your left roughly halfway along, you will come across the area for hiring equipment."},{"id":"q4","correct_answer":"C","acceptable_answers":["C"],"score":1,"explanation":"The spectator seating is further along on the left-hand side before the North Gate, at mid-level on the left, which corresponds to label C.","transcript_evidence":"Further along on the left-hand side, before you reach the North Gate, is the spectator seating area."},{"id":"q5","correct_answer":"E","acceptable_answers":["E"],"score":1,"explanation":"The outdoor cafe (refreshments area) is in the top-left corner near the North Gate, which corresponds to label E. The transcript mentions that plans to move it did not proceed.","transcript_evidence":"On the far left as you face the gate is where you can get refreshments. There were plans to move this to the centre of the complex, but in the end it remained in the top-left corner."},{"id":"q6","correct_answer":"F","acceptable_answers":["F"],"score":1,"explanation":"The first aid point is in the top-right corner, just before the North Gate on the far right, which corresponds to label F.","transcript_evidence":"On the far right, just before the North Gate, is where you will find the first aid point, which is staffed during all opening hours."}],"thumbnail":null,"map_image":null,"type":"map_labelling","topic":null,"tests_taken":"0","level":"B2","audio_file":[]}	{"status":"published"}	\N	\N
