216	250	listening_tests	ac2babeb-afbd-499a-9cac-10238c31e1b7	{"status":"draft","title":"Village Facilities Map","slug":"village-facilities-map","description":"A map labelling listening practice about facilities in a village.","type":"map_labelling","level":"medium","accent":"british","duration_seconds":188,"question_count":5,"is_free":true,"instruction_text":"Label the map below. Write the correct letter, A-H, next to Questions 1-5.","transcript":"Welcome to everyone here. I hope you enjoy your stay in our village and enjoy the local scenery. I’ll tell you a bit about the forest and mountain tracks in a minute, but first, I’ll just give you an idea of where everything is in the village. So, we’re here in the tourist information centre, and when you come out of the centre, you're on Willow Lane, just opposite the pond. If you want to get to the supermarket for your supplies of food and water, go right, that's the quickest way, and then turn right at the top of Willow Lane, and it's the second building you come to opposite the old railway station. If you're planning on doing some serious climbing and you need some equipment, we do have an excellent climbing supplies store just five minutes' walk away. Turn left once you're outside the tourist information centre, take Willow Lane all the way up to Pine Street - you want to go left along here - then keep walking and go past Mountain Road on your right, until you come to the next turning on the left - head down there, and you'll come to the climbing supplies store. If you get to the small building that sells ski passes, you'll know you've gone too far. You also need to head to Pine Street for the museum - it's small but well worth a visit if you're interested in the history of the village and the old gold mining industry. So, when you reach Pine Street from here, you'll see the old railway line on the other side of the road - turn left into Pine Street, and keep going until you come to Mountain Road, and just up here, the museum will be on your left, just behind the railway line. Don't worry about crossing over the tracks. The trains stopped running through here in 1985. If you're planning on following one of the easier forest walks, you might like to hire a bicycle. To get to the hire shop, again you need to head to Pine Street. On the left-hand side of Pine Street, you'll see the Town Hall, go down the little road that you come to just before it, and you'll find the bike hire shop just behind the hall. They have a good range of bikes so I'm sure you'll find something that suits your needs. Last but not least, if you're hungry after a long day's trek I can recommend our local café. Again, when you leave the tourist information centre, turn right and follow Willow Lane until it joins Pine Street - and right opposite - on the far side of the railway tracks - is the café.","prosody_script":null,"questions_public_json":{"groups":[{"id":"g1","type":"map_labelling","title":"Questions 1-5","instruction":"Label the map below. Write the correct letter, A-H, next to Questions 1-5.","question_range":{"from":1,"to":5},"media":{"type":"image","field":"image_file"},"options":{"type":"letters","values":["A","B","C","D","E","F","G","H"]},"questions":[{"id":"q1","number":1,"text":"Supermarket","input_type":"select"},{"id":"q2","number":2,"text":"Climbing supplies store","input_type":"select"},{"id":"q3","number":3,"text":"Museum","input_type":"select"},{"id":"q4","number":4,"text":"Bike hire shop","input_type":"select"},{"id":"q5","number":5,"text":"Café","input_type":"select"}]}]},"questions_answer_json":{"answers":[{"question_id":"q1","correct_answer":"G","acceptable_answers":["G"],"explanation":"The supermarket is reached by going right from the tourist information centre, then right at the top of Willow Lane. It is the second building opposite the old railway station, which is G.","transcript_evidence":"Go right, that's the quickest way, and then turn right at the top of Willow Lane, and it's the second building you come to opposite the old railway station."},{"question_id":"q2","correct_answer":"D","acceptable_answers":["D"],"explanation":"The climbing supplies store is reached by going left along Pine Street, past Mountain Road, then taking the next turning on the left. It is before the ski passes building, which places it at D.","transcript_evidence":"Keep walking and go past Mountain Road on your right, until you come to the next turning on the left - head down there, and you'll come to the climbing supplies store. If you get to the small building that sells ski passes, you'll know you've gone too far."},{"question_id":"q3","correct_answer":"A","acceptable_answers":["A"],"explanation":"The museum is on Pine Street near Mountain Road, on the left, just behind the railway line. This matches A.","transcript_evidence":"Turn left into Pine Street, and keep going until you come to Mountain Road, and just up here, the museum will be on your left, just behind the railway line."},{"question_id":"q4","correct_answer":"E","acceptable_answers":["E"],"explanation":"The bike hire shop is behind the Town Hall, reached by going down the small road just before it. This location is E.","transcript_evidence":"On the left-hand side of Pine Street, you'll see the Town Hall, go down the little road that you come to just before it, and you'll find the bike hire shop just behind the hall."},{"question_id":"q5","correct_answer":"C","acceptable_answers":["C"],"explanation":"The café is opposite Willow Lane on the far side of the railway tracks. This matches C.","transcript_evidence":"When you leave the tourist information centre, turn right and follow Willow Lane until it joins Pine Street - and right opposite - on the far side of the railway tracks - is the café."}]},"metadata":{"source_type":"uploaded_audio_and_map","visual_type":"village_map","map_listening_category":"map","task_format":"Label the map below. Write the correct letter, A-H, next to Questions 1-5.","answer_ke