grams, or semantic visual clues. Question-target and distractor locations must be visually neutral."},"image_generation_prompt":"A clean, simplified 2D map plan of Lakeside Park for a language exam. At the bottom centre, there is a clear text label reading Main Entrance. In the absolute centre of the map is a large circular water feature labelled Central Lake. A network of simple grey paths connects the entrance to a circular path surrounding the lake. There is a North Gate at the top. An Old Bridge is on the left path. There are eight neutral, identical rectangular plots scattered across the park grounds, each clearly marked with a single bold capital letter from A to H. Plot A is directly right of the Main Entrance. Plot B is between the entrance and the lake. Plot G is on the west path before the Old Bridge. Plot C is on the west path just after the Old Bridge. Plot D is on the east path next to the lake. Plot H is on the east path opposite D. Plot E is near the North Gate. Plot F is in the top right corner. The entire map contains no icons, no trees, no picnic tables, no boats, no coffee cups, and no signs. All structures are completely empty, neutral outlines to ensure functions cannot be guessed visually.","difficulty_notes":{"word_count":343,"visible_label_count":8,"question_count":6,"distractor_label_count":2,"why_this_level":"Contains changed locations (the old cafe), negations ('no longer open', 'don't go there'), and positional phrases typical of B2 such as 'far side of', 'just beyond', 'directly opposite', and 'before you reach'.","distractors":["The old cafe location near the entrance which is now staff parking.","The maintenance shed near the North Gate which could be mistaken for the cafe."],"key_phrases":["straight ahead","no longer open","instead","far side of","just beyond","directly opposite","before you reach","just past"],"visual_fairness_check":{"can_learners_guess_answers_from_image_alone":false,"anti_leak_checked":true,"notes":"Every letter label corresponds to an identical, completely featureless geometric shape. There are absolutely no signs, trees, tables, or icons depicting coffee cups, bicycles, or presents. The answers can only be determined by listening to the spatial directions in the talk."}},"audio_preparation":{"audio_engine":"ElevenLabs v3","needs_audio_script_conversion":true,"do_not_put_audio_tags_in_transcript":true,"transcript_style":"clean plain English"}},"map_image":null,"thumbnail":null}	\N	\N
