536	694	listening_tests	5aaa34d2-c34c-4c63-ba02-057f722e791f	{"status":"draft","title":"Using a Coffee Machine","slug":"using-a-coffee-machine","description":"A cross-section or external diagram of a home coffee machine.","type":"diagram_labelling","level":"A2","accent":"British","duration_seconds":null,"question_count":4,"is_free":true,"instruction_text":"Label the diagram below. Write the correct letter, A-D, next to Questions 1-4.","transcript":"Hello and welcome to your new coffee machine. Let me explain how to use it. First, look at the back of the machine. At the top, on the right side, you will find the water tank. Fill this with cold water. Next, look at the top left of the machine. This is the coffee bean hopper. Pour your fresh beans in here. Then, the machine will grind them for you. Now, in the centre, behind the main door, is the brewing chamber. This is where the hot water mixes with the coffee. You need to clean this part every week. Finally, look at the base of the machine, underneath the cups. This is the drip tray. It catches any spilled coffee, so remember to empty it regularly. Enjoy your coffee!","prosody_script":null,"questions_public_json":{"groups":[{"id":"g1","type":"diagram_labelling","title":"Questions 1-4","instruction":"Label the diagram below. Write the correct letter, A-D, next to Questions 1-4.","question_range":{"from":1,"to":4},"media":{"image":{"type":"image","field":"image_file"},"audio":{"type":"audio","field":"audio_file"}},"options":{"type":"letters","values":["A","B","C","D"]},"questions":[{"id":"q1","number":1,"text":"Water tank","input_type":"text","score":1},{"id":"q2","number":2,"text":"Coffee bean hopper","input_type":"text","score":1},{"id":"q3","number":3,"text":"Brewing chamber","input_type":"text","score":1},{"id":"q4","number":4,"text":"Drip tray","input_type":"text","score":1}]}]},"questions_answer_json":[{"id":"q1","correct_answer":"C","acceptable_answers":["C","c"],"score":1,"explanation":"The water tank is locate