550	713	listening_tests	d3307137-ae3c-4387-a33a-30b8d6a440d9	{"id":"d3307137-ae3c-4387-a33a-30b8d6a440d9","title":"Lakeside Park Facilities","slug":"lakeside-park-facilities","description":"An outdoor map of Lakeside Park featuring a central lake, entrances, paths, and various facilities.","accent":"British English","duration_seconds":null,"question_count":6,"is_free":true,"instruction_text":"Label the map below. Write the correct letter, A-H, next to Questions 1-6.","transcript":"Welcome everyone to Lakeside Park. I'm the head ranger, and I'd like to give you a quick overview of the park's layout so you can make the most of your visit today. You are all currently standing at the Main Entrance, looking into the park. Straight ahead of you, before you reach the lake, is a large building. This is the Visitor Centre. You can get detailed maps and information here. Now, many of you have asked about getting some food and drink. We used to have a small cafe just to the right of the Main Entrance, but that building is no longer open to the public; it's just for staff parking now. Instead, to find the new Cafe, you need to walk along the path that goes around the eastern side of the central lake. Keep walking right to the far side of the lake, and you'll find it near the North Gate. There's a building just beyond the cafe in the top corner, but don't go there as that's just a maintenance shed. If you are interested in renting out a rowing boat, the Boat Hire is also on the eastern side of the lake. Walk up the main east path, and it's right next to the water. Directly opposite the Boat Hire, on the other side of the east path, you'll see a beautiful area enclosed by hedges. This is the Rose Garden, which is currently in full bloom. Over on the western side of the park, there's plenty to do as well. As you walk up the west path from the Main Entrance, before you reach the Old Bridge, you'll see a large fenced-off area. This is the Children's Playground, which we recently expanded. Continuing further on the west path, you'll walk over the Old Bridge. Just past the bridge, on the left-hand side, is a lovely shaded spot. This is the Picnic Area, perfect for relaxing after a walk. We hope you have a wonderful day exploring Lakeside Park!","prosody_script":null,"date_created":"2026-06-10T14:42:52.557Z","date_updated":"2026-06-10T14:42:52.557Z","status":"published","metadata":{"schema_version":"visual_labelling_listening_v1","topic":"Lakeside Park","speaker_role":"Park Guide","visual_blueprint":{"visual_type":"map_labelling","description":"An outdoor map of Lakeside Park featuring a central lake, entrances, paths, and various facilities.","canvas_layout":"The Main Entrance is at the bottom centre. A path leads straight ahead towards the central lake. Paths diverge to go around the east and west sides of the lake. There is an Old Bridge on the west path. The North Gate is at the top centre.","fixed_orientation_landmarks":[{"name":"Main Entrance","position":"Bottom centre","visible_text_on_image":"Main Entrance","why_safe_to_show":"Starting point for orientation."},{"name":"Central Lake","position":"Middle of the map","visible_text_on_image":"Central Lake","why_safe_to_show":"Major geographical feature used for relative spatial directions."},{"name":"North Gate","position":"Top centre","visible_text_on_image":"North Gate","why_safe_to_show":"Orientation point at the top of the map."},{"name":"The Old Bridge","position":"On the west path crossing a small stream","visible_text_on_image":"Old Bridge","why_safe_to_show":"Reference point for navigation on the west path."}],"visible_labels":[{"label":"A","position":"Just to the right of the Main Entrance","is_answer_label":false,"hidden_correct_place_or_part":"Staff Parking (former cafe)","visual_appearance":"neutral shape only","visual_neutrality_rule":"Do not reveal this answer or distractor through icons, objects, signs, products, tools, furniture, symbols, vehicles, or semantic visual clues."},{"label":"B","position":"Straight ahead from the Main Entrance, just before the Central Lake","is_answer_label":true,"hidden_correct_place_or_part":"Visitor Centre","visual_appearance":"neutral shape only","visual_neutrality_rule":"Do not reveal this answer or distractor through icons, objects, signs, products, tools, furniture, symbols, vehicles, or semantic visual clues."},{"label":"C","position":"On the west path, just past the Old Bridge","is_answer_label":true,"hidden_correct_place_or_part":"Picnic Area","visual_appearance":"neutral shape only","visual_neutrality_rule":"Do not reveal this answer or distractor through icons, objects, signs, products, tools, furniture, symbols, vehicles, or semantic visual clues."},{"label":"D","position":"On the east path, right next to the water of the Central Lake","is_answer_label":true,"hidden_correct_place_or_part":"Boat Hire","visual_appearance":"neutral shape only","visual_neutrality_rule":"Do not reveal this answer or distractor through icons, objects, signs, products, tools, furniture, symbols, vehicles, or semantic visual clues."},{"label":"E","position":"On the far side of the lake, near the North Gate","is_answer_label":true,"hidden_correct_place_or_part":"Cafe","visual_appearance":"neutral shape only","visual_neutrality_rule":"Do not reveal this answer or distractor through icons, objects, signs, products, tools, furniture, symbols, vehicles, or semantic visual clues."},{"label":"F","position":"In the top right corner, just beyond label E","is_answer_label":false,"hidden_correct_place_or_part":"Maintenance Shed","visual_appearance":"neutral shape only","visual_neutrality_rule":"Do not reveal this answer or distractor through icons, objects, signs, products, tools, furniture, symbols, vehicles, or semantic visual clues."},{"label":"G","position":"On the west path, before reaching the Old Bridge","is_answer_label":true,"hidden_correct_place_or_part":"Children's Playground","visual_appearance":"neutral shape only","visual_neutrality_rule":"Do not reveal this answer or distractor through icons, objects, signs, products, tools, furniture, symbols, vehicles, or semantic visual clues."},{"label":"H","position":"On the east path, directly opposite label D, away from the water","is_answer_label":true,"hidden_correct_place_or_part":"Rose Garden","visual_appearance":"neutral shape only","visual_neutrality_rule":"Do not reveal this answer or distractor through icons, objects, signs, products, tools, furniture, symbols, vehicles, or semantic visual clues."}],"image_rule":"The image must show fixed orientation landmarks and visible letter labels only. Do not print correct answer names on the image. Do not reveal answer or distractor locations through icons, products, furniture, tools, signs, logos, vehicles, pictograms, or semantic visual clues. Question-target and distractor locations must be visually neutral."},"image_generation_prompt":"A clean, simplified 2D map plan of Lakeside Park for a language exam. At the bottom centre, there is a clear text label reading Main Entrance. In the absolute centre of the map is a large circular water feature labelled Central Lake. A network of simple grey paths connects the entrance to a circular path surrounding the lake. There is a North Gate at the top. An Old Bridge is on the left path. There are eight neutral, identical rectangular plots scattered across the park grounds, each clearly marked with a single bold capital letter from A to H. Plot A is directly right of the Main Entrance. Plot B is between the entrance and the lake. Plot G is on the west path before the Old Bridge. Plot C is on the west path just after the Old Bridge. Plot D is on the east path next to the lake. Plot H is on the east path opposite D. Plot E is near the North Gate. Plot F is in the top right corner. The entire map contains no icons, no trees, no picnic tables, no boats, no coffee cups, and no signs. All structures are completely empty, neutral outlines to ensure functions cannot be guessed visually.","difficulty_notes":{"word_count":343,"visible_label_count":8,"question_count":6,"distractor_label_count":2,"why_this_level":"Contains changed locations (the old cafe), negations ('no longer open', 'don't go there'), and positional phrases typical of B2 such as 'far side of', 'just beyond', 'directly opposite', and 'before you reach'.","distractors":["The old cafe location near the entrance which is now staff parking.","The maintenance shed near the North Gate which could be mistaken for the cafe."],"key_phrases":["straight ahead","no longer open","instead","far side of","just beyond","directly opposite","before you reach","just past"],"visual_fairness_check":{"can_learners_guess_answers_from_image_alone":false,"anti_leak_checked":true,"notes":"Every letter label corresponds to an identical, completely featureless geometric shape. There are absolutely no signs, trees, tables, or icons depicting coffee cups, bicycles, or presents. The answers can only be determined by listening to the spatial directions in the talk."}},"audio_preparation":{"audio_engine":"ElevenLabs v3","needs_audio_script_conversion":true,"do_not_put_audio_tags_in_transcript":true,"transcript_style":"clean plain English"}},"questions_public_json":{"groups":[{"id":"g1","type":"map_labelling","title":"Questions 1-6","instruction":"Label the map below. Write the correct letter, A-H, next to Questions 1-6.","question_range":{"from":1,"to":6},"media":{"image":{"type":"image","field":"image_file"},"audio":{"type":"audio","field":"audio_file"}},"options":{"type":"letters","values":["A","B","C","D","E","F","G","H"]},"questions":[{"id":"q1","number":1,"text":"Visitor Centre","input_type":"select","score":1},{"id":"q2","number":2,"text":"Cafe","input_type":"select","score":1},{"id":"q3","number":3,"text":"Boat Hire","input_type":"select","score":1},{"id":"q4","number":4,"text":"Rose Garden","input_type":"select","score":1},{"id":"q5","number":5,"text":"Children's Playground","input_type":"select","score":1},{"id":"q6","number":6,"text":"Picnic Area","input_type":"select","score":1}]}]},"questions_answer_json":[{"id":"q1","correct_answer":"B","acceptable_answers":["B"],"score":1,"explanation":"The Visitor Centre is the large building straight ahead from the Main Entrance, just before you reach the Central Lake, marked as label B.","transcript_evidence":"Straight ahead of you, before you reach the lake, is a large building. This is the Visitor Centre."},{"id":"q2","correct_answer":"E","acceptable_answers":["E"],"score":1,"explanation":"The new Cafe is on the far side of the Central Lake near the North Gate, marked as label E. The old cafe location near the entrance is now staff parking.","transcript_evidence":"Instead, to find the new Cafe, you need to walk along the path that goes around the eastern side of the central lake. Keep walking right to the far side of the lake, and you'll find it near the North Gate."},{"id":"q3","correct_answer":"D","acceptable_answers":["D"],"score":1,"explanation":"The Boat Hire is on the eastern side of the lake, right next to the water, marked as label D.","transcript_evidence":"Walk up the main east path, and it's right next to the water."},{"id":"q4","correct_answer":"H","acceptable_answers":["H"],"score":1,"explanation":"The Rose Garden is directly opposite the Boat Hire on the other side of the east path, away from the water, marked as label H.","transcript_evidence":"Directly opposite the Boat Hire, on the other side of the east path, you'll see a beautiful area enclosed by hedges. This is the Rose Garden."},{"id":"q5","correct_answer":"G","acceptable_answers":["G"],"score":1,"explanation":"The Children's Playground is on the west path from the Main Entrance, before you reach the Old Bridge, marked as label G.","transcript_evidence":"As you walk up the west path from the Main Entrance, before you reach the Old Bridge, you'll see a large fenced-off area. This is the Children's Playground."},{"id":"q6","correct_answer":"C","acceptable_answers":["C"],"score":1,"explanation":"The Picnic Area is on the west path just past the Old Bridge, on the left-hand side, marked as label C.","transcript_evidence":"you'll walk over the Old Bridge. Just past the bridge, on the left-hand side, is a lovely shaded spot. This is the Picnic Area."}],"thumbnail":null,"map_image":"59f48e30-bf9a-461f-aa04-299159676b9a","type":"map_labelling","topic":null,"tests_taken":"0","level":"medium","audio_file":[7]}	{"level":"medium"}	\N	\N
