555	718	listening_tests	ac2babeb-afbd-499a-9cac-10238c31e1b7	{"id":"ac2babeb-afbd-499a-9cac-10238c31e1b7","title":"Village Facilities Map","slug":"village-facilities-map","description":"A map labelling listening practice about facilities in a village.","accent":"british","duration_seconds":188,"question_count":5,"is_free":true,"instruction_text":"Label the map below. Write the correct letter, A-H, next to Questions 1-5.","transcript":"Welcome to everyone here. I hope you enjoy your stay in our village and enjoy the local scenery. I’ll tell you a bit about the forest and mountain tracks in a minute, but first, I’ll just give you an idea of where everything is in the village. So, we’re here in the tourist information centre, and when you come out of the centre, you're on Willow Lane, just opposite the pond. If you want to get to the supermarket for your supplies of food and water, go right, that's the quickest way, and then turn right at the top of Willow Lane, and it's the second building you come to opposite the old railway station. If you're planning on doing some serious climbing and you need some equipment, we do have an excellent climbing supplies store just five minutes' walk away. Turn left once you're outside the tourist information centre, take Willow Lane all the way up to Pine Street - you want to go left along here - then keep walking and go past Mountain Road on your right, until you come to the next turning on the left - head down there, and you'll come to the climbing supplies store. If you get to the small building that sells ski passes, you'll know you've gone too far. You also need to head to Pine Street for the museum - it's small but well worth a visit if you're interested in the history of the village and the old gold mining industry. So, when you reach Pine Street from here, you'll see the old railway line on the other side of the road - turn left into Pine Street, and keep going until you come to Mountain Road, and just up here, the museum will be on your left, just behind the railway line. Don't worry about crossing over the tracks. The trains stopped running through here in 1985. If you're planning on following one of the easier forest walks, you might like to hire a bicycle. To get to the hire shop, again you need to head to Pine Street. On the left-hand side of Pine Street, you'll see the Town Hall, go down the little road that you come to just before it, and you'll find the bike hire shop just behind the hall. They have a good range of bikes so I'm sure you'll find something that suits your needs. Last but not least, if you're hungry after a long day's trek I can recommend our local café. Again, when you leave the tourist information centre, turn right and follow Willow Lane until it joins Pine Street - and right opposite - on the far side of the railway tracks - is the café.","prosody_script":null,"date_created":"2026-05-31T06:48:30.510Z","date_updated":"2026-05-31T06:48:30.510Z","status":"published","metadata":{"source_type":"uploaded_audio_and_map","visual_type":"village_map","map_listening_category":"map","task_format":"Label the map below. Write the correct letter, A-H, next to Questions 1-5.","answer_key":{"1":"G","2":"D","3":"A","4":"E","5":"C"},"map_labels":["A","B","C","D","E","F","G","H"],"needs_review":true,"audio_duration_seconds_detected":188},"questions_public_json":{"groups":[{"id":"g1","type":"map_labelling","title":"Questions 1-5","instruction":"Label the map below. Write the correct letter, A-H, next to Questions 1-5.","question_range":{"from":1,"to":5},"media":{"type":"image","field":"image_file"},"options":{"type":"letters","values":["A","B","C","D","E","F","G","H"]},"questions":[{"id":"q1","number":1,"text":"Supermarket","input_type":"select"},{"id":"q2","number":2,"text":"Climbing supplies store","input_type":"select"},{"id":"q3","number":3,"text":"Museum","input_type":"select"},{"id":"q4","number":4,"text":"Bike hire shop","input_type":"select"},{"id":"q5","number":5,"text":"Café","input_type":"select"}]}]},"questions_answer_json":{"answers":[{"question_id":"q1","correct_answer":"G","acceptable_answers":["G"],"explanation":"The supermarket is reached by going right from the tourist information centre, then right at the top of Willow Lane. It is the second building opposite the old railway station, which is G.","transcript_evidence":"Go right, that's the quickest way, and then turn right at the top of Willow Lane, and it's the second building you come to opposite the old railway station."},{"question_id":"q2","correct_answer":"D","acceptable_answers":["D"],"explanation":"The climbing supplies store is reached by going left along Pine Street, past Mountain Road, then taking the next turning on the left. It is before the ski passes building, which places it at D.","transcript_evidence":"Keep walking and go past Mountain Road on your right, until you come to the next turning on the left - head down there, and you'll come to the climbing supplies store. If you get to the small building that sells ski passes, you'll know you've gone too far."},{"question_id":"q3","correct_answer":"A","acceptable_answers":["A"],"explanation":"The museum is on Pine Street near Mountain Road, on the left, just behind the railway line. This matches A.","transcript_evidence":"Turn left into Pine Street, and keep going until you come to Mountain Road, and just up here, the museum will be on your left, just behind the railway line."},{"question_id":"q4","correct_answer":"E","acceptable_answers":["E"],"explanation":"The bike hire shop is behind the Town Hall, reached by going down the small road just before it. This location is E.","transcript_evidence":"On the left-hand side of Pine Street, you'll see the Town Hall, go down the little road that you come to just before it, and you'll find the bike hire shop just behind the hall."},{"question_id":"q5","correct_answer":"C","acceptable_answers":["C"],"explanation":"The café is opposite Willow Lane on the far side of the railway tracks. This matches C.","transcript_evidence":"When you leave the tourist information centre, turn right and follow Willow Lane until it joins Pine Street - and right opposite - on the far side of the railway tracks - is the café."}]},"thumbnail":null,"map_image":"b5e32d61-4078-49d6-aee8-36cc133cdb2a","type":"map_labelling","topic":null,"tests_taken":"0","level":"basic","audio_file":[4]}	{"level":"basic"}	\N	\N
556	719	listening_tests	ea08e7e0-f0b6-45c4-b020-14ceb3f7aaea	{"id":"ea08e7e0-f0b6-45c4-b020-14ceb3f7aaea","title":"College Map - Facilities","slug":"college-map-facilities","description":"A map labelling listening practice about locations inside a college","accent":"british","duration_seconds":null,"question_count":0,"is_free":true,"instruction_text":null,"transcript":null,"prosody_script":null,"date_created":"2026-05-30T12:19:13.663Z","date_updated":"2026-05-30T12:19:13.663Z","status":"published","metadata":{"source_type":"uploaded_audio_and_map","map_labels":["A","B","C","D","E","F","G","H","I","J","K"],"task_format":"Write the correct letter, A-K, next to Questions 1-3.","estimated_level_reason":"Basic map labelling with only 3 questions and clear letter options.","needs_review":true},"questions_public_json":{"groups":[{"id":"g1","type":"map_labelling","title":"Questions 1-3","instruction":"Write the correct letter, A-K, next to Questions 1-3.","question_range":{"from":1,"to":3},"media":{"type":"image","field":"image_file"},"options":{"type":"letters","values":["A","B","C","D","E","F","G","H","I","J","K"]},"questions":[{"id":"q1","number":1,"text":"Administration office","input_type":"select"},{"id":"q2","number":2,"text":"Café","input_type":"select"},{"id":"q3","number":3,"text":"Student common room","input_type":"select"}]}]},"questions_answer_json":{"answers":[{"question_id":"q1","correct_answer":null,"acceptable_answers":[],"explanation":"","transcript_evidence":""},{"question_id":"q2","correct_answer":null,"acceptable_answers":[],"explanation":"","transcript_evidence":""},{"question_id":"q3","correct_answer":null,"acceptable_answers":[],"explanation":"","transcript_evidence":""}]},"thumbnail":null,"map_image":"0efdda83-9884-423c-9e1b-eb17d5be8f57","type":"map_labelling","topic":null,"tests_taken":"0","level":"basic","audio_file":[1]}	{"level":"basic"}	\N	\N
557	731	listening_tests	b0b3b578-0528-40a2-81fa-b1b844fab854	{"status":"draft","title":"Welcome to the Playverse","slug":"welcome-to-the-playverse","description":"An indoor floor plan of the Playverse Children's Activity Centre with a central Play Arena, lobby, corridors, and surrounding activity rooms.","type":"plan_labelling","level":"C1","accent":"British English","duration_seconds":null,"question_count":7,"is_free":true,"instruction_text":"Label the plan below. Write the correct letter, A-J, next to Questions 1-7.","transcript":"Hey everyone! Welcome to the brand-new Playverse Children's Activity Centre! I'm Leo, the lead coordinator here, and I'm super stoked to show you around our fresh, high-energy space today. We've designed this place to be the ultimate fun zone, but with ten different spaces, it's easy to get a bit lost, so let's get you oriented. Right now, we're all standing in the main lobby, just inside the Entrance at the bottom of your map. Right in the dead centre of the building, you can't miss our massive Play Arena—that's the huge circular structure with the slides and ball pits. Now, if you want to drop off your gear, take a look at the corridor going off to the left of the entrance. On the right side of this hallway, sharing a wall with the lobby, you'll see a room. We originally earmarked this for the administration staff, but we changed our minds and turned it into the Lockers and Cubbies, so feel free to store your bags there. Directly opposite those lockers, on the outer left-hand wall of the building, is a peaceful space called the Quiet Sensory Room. It's got soft lighting and bubble tubes, perfect if your kids need a quick breather from all the excitement. If you head all the way to the end of that left corridor, right into the top-left corner, you'll find the Art and Craft Zone. We've got easels, clay, and face painting set up there today. Now, walking out of the art zone along the top wall of the centre, there's a row of rooms. The one immediately on the right of the art zone is the Birthday Party Room. It's got a sliding door and is currently being decorated for a double birthday bash later this afternoon. Right next to that, still along the back wall, is our Climbing Wall, which features interactive projection games on the climbing surface. Oh, and just to the right of the climbing wall—before you get to the Cafe area—is a small room. Many kids try to wander in there thinking it's part of the play area, but that's actually the Staff Office, so it's strictly off-limits. Speaking of the Cafe, that's located in the top-right corner of the layout, right next to the seating area. If you're looking for a spot to relax, parents can also hang out in the Parents' Lounge, which is that open-plan zone on the left of the central Play Arena. Just behind the Parents' Lounge, on the left side of the map, is Toddler Town, which is fully padded and reserved exclusively for toddlers under three. Lastly, let's cover the right side of the building. If you walk down the corridor to the right of the main entrance, the first room you encounter on the right, along the outer wall, is the Virtual Reality Zone. We've got some cool motion-simulator chairs in there. Further up this right-hand corridor, just before you enter the Cafe, there's a room on the left side of the hallway, facing the central Play Arena. This is the Toy Library, where you can borrow board games or educational toys. And finally, if you go all the way past the Cafe to the very top right, tucked away behind the main cafe counter, is the First Aid Station, which we hope you won't have to visit! Alright, that's the grand tour! Have an awesome time, and let's get playing!","prosody_script":null,"questions_public_json":{"groups":[{"id":"g1","type":"plan_labelling","title":"Questions 1-7","instruction":"Label the plan below. Write the correct letter, A-J, next to Questions 1-7.","question_range":{"from":1,"to":7},"media":{"image":{"type":"image","field":"image_file"},"audio":{"type":"audio","field":"audio_file"}},"options":{"type":"letters","values":["A","B","C","D","E","F","G","H","I","J"]},"questions":[{"id":"q1","number":1,"text":"Quiet Sensory Room","input_type":"select","score":1},{"id":"q2","number":2,"text":"Art and Craft Zone","input_type":"select","score":1},{"id":"q3","number":3,"text":"Birthday Party Room","input_type":"select","score":1},{"id":"q4","number":4,"text":"Climbing Wall","input_type":"select","score":1},{"id":"q5","number":5,"text":"Toddler Town","input_type":"select","score":1},{"id":"q6","number":6,"text":"Virtual Reality Zone","input_type":"select","score":1},{"id":"q7","number":7,"text":"Toy Library","input_type":"select","score":1}]}]},"questions_answer_json":[{"id":"q1","correct_answer":"C","acceptable_answers":["C"],"score":1,"explanation":"The Quiet Sensory Room is located along the left corridor immediately on entering, on the outer left-hand wall, which is opposite the lockers, marked as label C.","transcript_evidence":"Directly opposite those lockers, on the outer left-hand wall of the building, is a peaceful space called the Quiet Sensory Room."},{"id":"q2","correct_answer":"A","acceptable_answers":["A"],"score":1,"explanation":"The Art and Craft Zone is at the very end of the left corridor, in the top-left corner, marked as label A.","transcript_evidence":"If you head all the way to the end of that left corridor, right into the top-left corner, you'll find the Art and Craft Zone."},{"id":"q3","correct_answer":"E","acceptable_answers":["E"],"score":1,"explanation":"The Birthday Party Room is along the top wall, immediately to the right of the Art and Craft Zone, marked as label E.","transcript_evidence":"Now, walking out of the art zone along the top wall of the centre, there's a row of rooms. The one immediately on the right of the art zone is the Birthday Party Room."},{"id":"q4","correct_answer":"F","acceptable_answers":["F"],"score":1,"explanation":"The Climbing Wall is along the