nding activity rooms.","type":"plan_labelling","level":"C1","accent":"British English","duration_seconds":null,"question_count":7,"is_free":true,"instruction_text":"Label the plan below. Write the correct letter, A-J, next to Questions 1-7.","transcript":"Hey everyone! Welcome to the brand-new Playverse Children's Activity Centre! I'm Leo, the lead coordinator here, and I'm super stoked to show you around our fresh, high-energy space today. We've designed this place to be the ultimate fun zone, but with ten different spaces, it's easy to get a bit lost, so let's get you oriented. Right now, we're all standing in the main lobby, just inside the Entrance at the bottom of your map. Right in the dead centre of the building, you can't miss our massive Play Arena—that's the huge circular structure with the slides and ball pits. Now, if you want to drop off your gear, take a look at the corridor going off to the left of the entrance. On the right side of this hallway, sharing a wall with the lobby, you'll see a room. We originally earmarked this for the administration staff, but we changed our minds and turned it into the Lockers and Cubbies, so feel free to store your bags there. Directly opposite those lockers, on the outer left-hand wall of the building, is a peaceful space called the Quiet Sensory Room. It's got soft lighting and bubble tubes, perfect if your kids need a quick breather from all the excitement. If you head all the way to the end of that left corridor, right into the top-left corner, you'll find the Art and Craft Zone. We've got easels, clay, and face painting set up there today. Now, walking out of the art zone along the top wall of the centre, there's a row of rooms. The one immediately on the right of the art zone is the Birthday Party Room. It's got a sliding door and is currently being decorated for a double birthday bash later this afternoon. Right next to that, still along the back wall, is our Climbing Wall, which features interactive projection games on the climbing surface. Oh, and just to the right of the climbing wall—before you get to the Cafe area—is a small room. Many kids try to wander in there thinking it's part of the play area, but that's actually the Staff Office, so it's strictly off-limits. Speaking of the Cafe, that's located in the top-right corner of the layout, right next to the seating area. If you're looking for a spot to relax, parents can also hang out in the Parents' Lounge, which is that open-plan zone on the left of the central Play Arena. Just behind the Parents' Lounge, on the left side of the map, is Toddler Town, which is fully padded and reserved exclusively for toddlers under three. Lastly, let's cover the right side of the building. If you walk down the corridor to the right of the main entrance, the first room you encounter on the right, along the outer wall, is the Virtual Reality Zone. We've got some cool motion-simulator chairs in there. Further up this right-hand corridor, just before you enter the Cafe, there's a room on the left side of the hallway, facing the central Play Arena. This is the Toy Library, where you can borrow board games or educational toys. And finally, if you go all the way past the Cafe to the very top right, tucked away behind the main cafe counter, is the First Aid Station, which we hope you won't have to visit! Alright, that's the grand tour! Have an awesome time, and let's get playing!","prosody_script":null,"questions_public_json":{"groups":[{"id":"g1","type":"plan_labelling","title":"Questions 1-7","instruction":"Label the plan below. Write the correct letter, A-J, next to Questions 1-7.","question_range":{"from":1,"to":7},"media":{"image":{"type":"image","field":"image_file"},"audio":{"type":"audio","field":"audio_file"}},"options":{"type":"letters","values":["A","B","C","D","E","F","G","H","I","J"]},"questions":[{"id":"q1","number":1,"text":"Quiet Sensory Room","input_type":"select","score":1},{"id":"q2","number":2,"text":"Art and Craft Zone"