722	956	listening_tests	cf29994c-9181-4ed1-924f-f7bfb259202e	{"id":"cf29994c-9181-4ed1-924f-f7bfb259202e","title":"Organic Farm Layout","slug":"organic-farm-layout","description":"An outdoor map of an Organic Farm featuring a central pond, paths, and various locations.","accent":"British English","duration_seconds":null,"question_count":5,"is_free":true,"instruction_text":"Label the map below. Write the correct letter, A-F, next to Questions 1-5.","transcript":"Welcome to our organic farm. I'm delighted to show you around today. We're currently standing at the Main Entrance. If you look straight ahead, you'll see a path leading to the central pond in the middle of the farm. First, on your left, just past the entrance, is our Farm Shop. You can buy fresh produce and honey here at the end of your visit. Opposite that, on the right side of the path, is a building, but that is actually the tool shed, which is only for staff, so please do not enter. As you continue up the path, walk past the central pond. On your left, just past the pond, you will find the Herb Garden, where we grow culinary and medicinal herbs. Across the path from the Herb Garden, directly opposite it, is the Tomato Greenhouse, where we cultivate organic tomatoes. Further along, at the top-right corner of the farm, past the greenhouse, you'll find the Beehives. Our bees are essential for pollinating the crops. Finally, if you head to the far north-west corner, just beyond the Herb Garden, you'll reach the Compost Area, where we recycle all our organic waste. Enjoy your tour!","prosody_script":null,"date_created":"2026-06-17T01:13:47.596Z","date_updated":"2026-06-17T01:13:47.596Z","status":"published","metadata":{"schema_version":"visual_labelling_listening_v1","topic":"Organic Farm","speaker_role":"Farm Guide","image_generation_prompt":"A clean, simplified 2D map plan of an Organic Farm for a language exam. At the bottom centre, there is a clear text label reading 'Main Entrance'. In the absolute centre of the map is a small circular water feature labelled 'Central Pond'. A straight grey path connects the entrance to the pond, and branches go north, east, and west. There are six neutral, identical rectangular plots, each clearly marked with a single bold capital letter from A to F. Plot A is on the left side of the entrance path. Plot B is on the right side of the entrance path. Plot C is near the top-left, just past the pond. Plot D is to the right (east) of the pond. Plot E is at the top-right corner. Plot F is at the far north-west corner. The entire map is set against a white background, completely free of icons, trees, beehives, compost bins, greenhouses, tools, or decorative elements.","difficulty_notes":{"word_count":193,"visible_label_count":6,"question_count":5,"distractor_label_count":1,"why_this_level":"Contains standard B1 spatial language like 'past', 'opposite', 'directly opposite', 'beyond', 'far corner', and 'top-right corner'. Word count is 193 words, which is within the 180-260 word range. Features 1 distractor label (B, the tool shed).","distractors":["The tool shed (label B) near the entrance which is only for staff."],"key_phrases":["just past","opposite","past the pond","directly opposite","beyond"],"visual_fairness_check":{"can_learners_guess_answers_from_image_alone":false,"anti_leak_checked":true,"notes":"Every letter label corresponds to a completely featureless, identical plot. There are no signs, icons, or visual clues to guess which label is the greenhouse, herb garden, farm shop, beehives, or compost area."}}},"questions_public_json":{"groups":[{"id":"g1","type":"map_labelling","title":"Questions 1-5","instruction":"Label the map below. Write the correct letter, A-F, next to Questions 1-5.","question_range":{"from":1,"to":5},"media":{"image":{"type":"image","field":"image_file"},"audio":{"type":"audio","field":"audio_file"}},"options":{"type":"letters","values":["A","B","C","D","E","F"]},"questions":[{"id":"q1","number":1,"text":"Farm Shop","input_type":"select","score":1},{"id":"q2","number":2,"text":"Herb Garden","input_type":"select","score":1},{"id":"q3","number":3,"text":"Tomato Greenhouse","input_type":"select","score":1},{"id":"q4","number":4,"text":"Beehives","input_type":"select","score":1},{"id":"q5","number":5,"text":"Compost Area","input_type":"select","score":1}]}]},"questions_answer_json":[{"id":"q1","correct_answer":"A","acceptable_answers":["A"],"score":1,"explanation":"The Farm Shop is located just past the entrance on the left-hand side, which corresponds to label A.","transcript_evidence":"First, on your left, just past the entrance, is our Farm Shop."},{"id":"q2","correct_answer":"C","acceptable_answers":["C"],"score":1,"explanation":"The Herb Garden is located just past the pond on the left-hand side, which corresponds to label C.","transcript_evidence":"On your left, just past the pond, you will find the Herb Garden"},{"id":"q3","correct_answer":"D","acceptable_answers":["D"],"score":1,"explanation":"The Tomato Greenhouse is directly opposite the Herb Garden on the other side of the path, which corresponds to label D.","transcript_evidence":"Across the path from the Herb Garden, directly opposite it, is the Tomato Greenhouse"},{"id":"q4","correct_answer":"E","acceptable_answers":["E"],"score":1,"explanation":"The Beehives are located at the top-right corner of the farm, past the greenhouse, which corresponds to label E.","transcript_evidence":"Further along, at the top-right corner of the farm, past the greenhouse, you'll find the Beehives."},{"id":"q5","correct_answer":"F","acceptable_answers":["F"],"score":1,"explanation":"The Compost Area is located in the far north-west corner, just beyond the Herb Garden, which corresponds to label F.","transcript_evidence":"Finally, if you head to the far north-west corner, just beyond the Herb Garden, you'll reach the Compost Area"}],"thumbnail":null,"map_image":"48fdba1c-e953-4834-8fca-39e69d92176b","type":"map_labelling","topic":null,"tests_taken":"0","level":"medium","audio_file":[10]}	{"level":"medium"}	\N	\N
