719	953	listening_tests	cf29994c-9181-4ed1-924f-f7bfb259202e	{"id":"cf29994c-9181-4ed1-924f-f7bfb259202e","title":"Organic Farm Layout","slug":"organic-farm-layout","description":"An outdoor map of an Organic Farm featuring a central pond, paths, and various locations.","accent":"British English","duration_seconds":null,"question_count":5,"is_free":true,"instruction_text":"Label the map below. Write the correct letter, A-F, next to Questions 1-5.","transcript":"Welcome to our organic farm. I'm delighted to show you around today. We're currently standing at the Main Entrance. If you look straight ahead, you'll see a path leading to the central pond in the middle of the farm. First, on your left, just past the entrance, is our Farm Shop. You can buy fresh produce and honey here at the end of your visit. Opposite that, on the right side of the path, is a building, but that is actually the tool shed, which is only for staff, so please do not enter. As you continue up the path, walk past the central pond. On your left, just past the pond, you will find the Herb Garden, where we grow culinary and medicinal herbs. Across the path from the Herb Garden, directly opposite it, is the Tomato Greenhouse, where we cultivate organic tomatoes. Further along, at the top-right corner of the farm, past the greenhouse, you'll find the Beehives. Our bees are essential for pollinating the crops. Finally, if you head to the far north-west corner, just beyond the Herb Garden, you'll reach the Compost Area, where we recycle all our organic waste. Enjoy your tour!","prosody_script":null,"date_created":"2026-06-17T01:13:47.596Z","date_updated":"2026-06-17T01:13:47.596Z","status":"published","metadata":{"schema_version":"visual_labelling_listening_v1","topic":"Organic Farm","speaker_role":"Farm Guide","image_generation_prompt":"A clean, simplified 2D map plan of an Organic Farm for a language exam. At the bottom centre, there is a clear text label reading 'Main Entrance'. In the absolute centr