ormation Booth and right along the western perimeter wall, you'll spot that pavilion. It features local microbreweries. Just next to the Information Booth, you'll notice a small ticket booth. We no longer use this since tickets are digital, so feel free to bypass it. Now, if we walk up the Main Path towards the center, we reach the Central Piazza, which has seating. Just before you get to the Piazza, on the left-hand side of the Main Path, is the Artisan Cheese Stall. It was originally going to be placed on the opposite side of the path, but we decided this spot near the shade of the large oak trees was much better. Continuing past the Piazza, straight ahead at the very top of the map, you’ll see the Main Stage, where live chef demonstrations will take place all day. If you go to the far North, directly behind the Main Stage, you’ll find the VIP Dining Area. This area is reserved for pass-holders and sponsors. To the left of the Main Stage, tucked into the far top-left corner of the site, is the International Food Court. You'll find cuisines from five different continents there. Now, let’s look at the eastern side of the festival site. If you walk from the entrance along the path heading east, or to your right, the first building you'll see in the bottom-right corner is the First Aid Post. We had originally set up the Volunteer Rest Zone there, but for safety reasons, we swapped them, so the first aid team is now right there, and the volunteer rest zone has been moved to the quieter spot directly behind it. Moving further north along that eastern path, about halfway up, is the Gourmet Dessert Stand, which is famous for its artisanal ice creams. Finally, if you keep going all the way to the top-right corner, next to the waste recycling area, you'll find the Vegetarian Kitchen, serving a fantastic selection of plant-based street food. Have a wonderful day tasting everything, and enjoy the festival!","prosody_script":null,"questions_public_json":{"groups":[{"id":"g1","