736	983	listening_tests	bd11f758-8a3e-4ccb-854d-6dfa2c7df8fb	{"id":"bd11f758-8a3e-4ccb-854d-6dfa2c7df8fb","title":"Welcome to the Riverside Food Festival","slug":"welcome-to-the-riverside-food-festival","description":"An outdoor map of the Riverside Food Festival grounds, featuring entrance gates, paths, a central Piazza, a Main Stage, and various food and drink stall locations.","accent":"British English","duration_seconds":null,"question_count":7,"is_free":true,"instruction_text":"Label the map below. Write the correct letter, A-J, next to Questions 1-7.","transcript":"Hello everyone, and a very warm welcome to the Annual Riverside Food Festival! I’m Sarah, your event director, and I’m delighted to guide you through our layout this year. We’ve expanded the festival grounds quite a bit, so please look at your maps while I explain where everything is. Right now, we are gathered at the main Entrance, located at the very bottom center of your map. Immediately to your left, just past the gates, you’ll see the Information Booth, where you can grab event guides and schedules. Let’s start with our first highlight: the Craft Beer Pavilion. If you look at the bottom-left corner of the map, just past the Information Booth and right along the western perimeter wall, you'll spot that pavilion. It features local microbreweries. Just next to the Information Booth, you'll notice a small ticket booth. We no longer use this since tickets are digital, so feel free to bypass it. Now, if we walk up the Main Path towards the center, we reach the Central Piazza, which has seating. Just before you get to the Piazza, on the left-hand side of the Main Path, is the Artisan Cheese Stall. It was originally going to be placed on the opposite side of the path, but we decided this spot near the shade of the large oak trees was much better. Continuing past the Piazza, straight ahead at the very top of the map, you’ll see the Main Stage, where live chef demonstrations will take place all day. If you go to the far North, directly behind the Main Stage, you’ll find the VIP Dining Area. This area is reserved for pass-holders and sponsors. To the left of the Main Stage, tucked into the far top-left corner of the site, is the International Food Court. You'll find cuisines from five different continents there. Now, let’s look at the eastern side of the festival site. If you walk from the entrance along the path heading east, or to your right, the first building you'll see in the bottom-right corner is the First Aid Post. We had originally set up the Volunteer Rest Zone there, but for safety reasons, we swapped them, so the first aid team is now right there, and the volunteer rest zone has been moved to the quieter spot directly behind it. Moving further north along that eastern path, about halfway up, is the Gourmet Dessert Stand, which is famous for its artisanal ice creams. Finally, if you keep going all the way to the top-right corner, next to the waste recycling area, you'll find the Vegetarian Kitchen, serving a fantastic selection of plant-based street food. Have a wonderful day tasting everything, and enjoy the festival!","prosody_script":null,"date_created":"2026-06-18T10:40:11.158Z","date_updated":"2026-06-18T10:40:11.158Z","status":"published","metadata":{"schema_version":"visual_labelling_listening_v1","topic":"Food Festival Site","speaker_role":"Event Director","image_generation_prompt":"A clean, minimalist 2D outdoor map layout of a Food Festival Site on a white background. At the bottom centre, there is a clear label 'Entrance' leading into a Main Path. To the left of the path, just inside, is a stall labelled 'Information Booth'. In the middle of the layout is a central square labelled 'Central Piazza'. At the top centre is a stage labelled 'Main Stage'. There are ten neutral, outline rectangles representing stall locations, each labelled with a bold capital letter from A to J. Plot C is in the bottom-left corner. Plot J is adjacent to the Informati