737	984	listening_tests	15c782fd-9623-46ce-9d4d-727eaf262d8f	{"status":"draft","title":"Tennis Club Grounds Tour","slug":"tennis-club-grounds-tour","description":"A bird's-eye map of a tennis club showing the full grounds including courts, pathways, a central club house, and various ancillary facilities arranged around the site. Ten neutral areas or buildings are labelled A through J. Only fixed orientation landmarks such as the Main Entrance, the Club House, and the numbered courts are visually identifiable. All other labelled locations appear as plain neutral blocks or areas.","type":"map_labelling","level":"C1","accent":"British English","duration_seconds":null,"question_count":7,"is_free":true,"instruction_text":"Label the map below. Write the correct letter, A-J, next to Questions 1-7.","transcript":"Welcome to Greenfield Tennis Club. My name is Sandra, and I'm the club administrator. I'll be taking you on a quick orientation of the grounds so that you know where everything is before your first session. We have quite a lot to cover, so do listen carefully.\\n\\nIf you're arriving by car, you'll want to note that the car parking area is located to the south-west of the site, just before you reach the Main Entrance. It's a generous open area and usually has plenty of space on weekday mornings. From there, you walk east along the perimeter path until you reach the Main Entrance gates.\\n\\nAs you come through the Main Entrance, the first thing you'll notice on your left — that's the western side as you walk in — is our equipment and apparel outlet. We stock rackets, balls, grips, and branded clothing. Players often pop in before a match to pick something up. That facility is on the left as you enter.\\n\\nOn your right as you come through the gate — so the eastern side — are the changing rooms. We have separate facilities for men and women, and there are secure lockers available. I'd encourage all new members to use the lockers rather than leaving valuables in bags at courtside.\\n\\nNow, if you walk north along the central path towards the Club House, you'll pass a small block on your right-hand side, roughly level with Court 2. That block is actually used for storing cleaning chemicals and groundskeeping supplies — it's not a member facility, so please don't go in there. Continuing past that, you reach the Club House itself.\\n\\nOn the eastern side of the Club House — right beside it to the north-east — we have a small room that is staffed during all opening hours by a qualified first-aider. This is an important facility and we're rather proud that we have it available every single day we're open. Please make a note of where it is.\\n\\nIf you head around to the back of the Club House — directly north — you'll find the office belonging to our head groundskeeper, Marcus. He manages court maintenance, oversees the irrigation schedule, and coordinates the volunteers who prepare the courts each morning. His office is tucked directly behind the Club House against the back fence, and he's always happy to take questions about court conditions.\\n\\nMoving over to the eastern courts, between Courts 4 and 5, right up against the east perimeter fence, we have a dedicated area for watching match play. This is particularly busy during our weekend tournaments and the annual club championship. It's a popular spot, so arrive early if you want a good view during competitive events.\\n\\nFinally, I want to tell you about our coaching facility. We run a full junior and adult coaching programme here at Greenfield, and the dedicated coaching space is in the north-west corner of the grounds, right next to Court 1. It has its own entrance from the western perimeter path. The lead coach, Rachel, runs sessions on Tuesday and Thursday evenings as well as Saturday mornings.\\n\\nThat covers the main areas. Please feel free to walk around and get your bearings before the induction session begins at half past two.","prosody_script":null,"questions_public_json":{"groups":[{"id":"g1","type":"map_labelling","title":"Questions 1-7","instruction":"Label the map below. Write the correct letter, A-J, next to Questions 1-7.","question_range":{"from":1,"to":7},"media":{"image":{"type":"image","field":"image_file"},"audio":{"type":"audio","field":"audio_file"}},"options":{"type":"letters","values":["A","B","C","D","E","F","G","H","I","J"]},"questions":[{"id":"q1","number":1,"text":"Car Park","input_type":"select","score":1},{"id":"q2","number":2,"text":"Pro Shop","input_type":"select","score":1},{"id":"q3","number":3,"text":"Changing Rooms","input_type":"select","score":1},{"id":"q4","number":4,"text":"First Aid Room","input_type":"select","score":1},{"id":"q5","number":5,"text":"Groundskeeper's Office","input_type":"select","score":1},{"id":"q6","number":6,"text":"Spectator Seating","input_type":"select","score":1},{"id":"q7","number":7,"text":"Coaching Academy","input_type":"select","score":1}]}]},"questions_answer_json":[{"id":"q1","correct_answer":"F","acceptable_answers":["F"],"score":1,"explanation":"The car parking area is in the south-west of the site, west of the Main Entrance, described as a generous open area reached before entering through the Main Entrance gates. This matches label F, which is positioned to the south-west outside the main courts area.","transcript_evidence":"the car parking area is located to the south-west of the site, just before you reach the Main Entrance. It's a generous open area and usually has plenty of space on weekday mornings."},{"id":"q2","correct_answer":"A","acceptable_answers":["A"],"score":1,"explanation":"The pro shop (described as the equipment and apparel outlet) is on the left as you enter through the Main Entrance, which is the western side. This corresponds to label A in the south-west corner beside the entrance on the left.","transcript_evidence":"the first thing you'll notice on your left — that's the western side as you walk in — is our equipment and apparel outlet. We stock rackets, balls, grips, and branded clothing."},{"id":"q3","correct_answer":"B","acceptable_answers":["B"],"score":1,"explanation":"The changing rooms are on the right as you come through the Main Entrance gate, meaning the eastern side. This corresponds to label B in the south-east corner beside the entrance on the right.","transcript_evidence":"On your right as you come through the gate — so the eastern side — are the changing rooms. We have separate facilities for men and women, and there are secure lockers available."},{"id":"q4","correct_answer":"H","acceptable_answers":["H"],"score":1,"explanation":"The first aid room is described as being on the eastern side of the Club House, directly beside it to the north-east. This matches label H positioned in the north-east corner beside the Club House.","transcript_evidence":"On the eastern side of the Club House — right beside it to the north-east — we have a small room that is staffed during all opening hours by a qualified first-aider."},{"id":"q5","correct_answer":"J","acceptable_answers":["J"],"score":1,"explanation":"The groundskeeper's office is located directly behind the Club House against the back (northern) fence. This matches label J, which is positioned on the north side directly behind the Club House against the northern perimeter fence.","transcript_evidence":"His office is tucked directly behind the Club House against the back fence, and he's always happy to take questions about court conditions."},{"id":"q6","correct_answer":"D","acceptable_answers":["D"],"score":1,"explanation":"The spectator seating area is described as being between Courts 4 and 5, right up against the east perimeter fence. This matches label D, positioned on the east side between Court 4 and Court 5 against the eastern perimeter fence.","transcript_evidence":"between Courts 4 and 5, right up against the east perimeter fence, we have a dedicated area for watching match play."},{"id":"q7","correct_answer":"E","acceptable_answers":["E"],"score":1,"explanation":"The coaching academy (described as the dedicated coaching space) is in the north-west corner of the grounds, right next to Court 1. This matches label E, which is positioned in the north-west corner beside Court 1 against the northern perimeter.","transcript_evidence":"the dedicated coaching space is in the north-west corner of the grounds, right next to Court 1. It has its own entrance from the western perimeter path."}],"metadata":{"schema_version":"visual_labelling_listening_v1","topic":"Tennis Club Grounds","speaker_role":"Club Administrator giving a guided orientation for new members","image_generation_prompt":"Create a clean bird's-eye map illustration of a tennis club grounds. The site is rectangular and enclosed by a perimeter fence. The Main Entrance is at the bottom-centre (south edge) — label it 'Main Entrance'. A wide central path leads from the entrance north to the Club House in the upper-centre of the map — label it 'Club House'. On the west side of the site, three rectangular tennis courts are arranged vertically: label them 'Court 1' (upper west), 'Court 2' (middle west), 'Court 3' (lower west). On the east side, three rectangular tennis courts are arranged vertically: label them 'Court 4' (upper east), 'Court 5' (middle east), 'Court 6' (lower east). Place ten neutral rectangular blocks or areas labelled A through J as follows: A — south-west corner, immediately left of the Main Entrance as you enter; B — south-east corner, immediately right of the Main Entrance as you enter; C — west side, below Court 3 near the south-west perimeter; D — east side, between Court 4 and Court 5 against the eastern fence; E — north-west corner, beside Court 1 against the northern fence; F — south side, west of the Main Entrance in the south-west as an open area; G — centre of the site, just north of the central path between the Club House and Court 2; H — north-east corner, beside the Club House on the east side; I — east side, south of Court 6 near the south-east perimeter; J — north side, directly behind the Club House against the northern perimeter fence. All labelled blocks and areas must be visually neutral plain shapes with only the letter label visible. Do not draw icons, signs, logos, pictograms, furniture, vehicles, tools, equipment, symbols, or any objects that suggest the function of any labelled location. Do not print any place names other than 'Main Entrance', 'Club House', 'Court 1', 'Court 2', 'Court 3', 'Court 4', 'Court 5', and 'Court 6' on the image. Learners must not be able to identify any labelled location without listening to the audio.","difficulty_notes":{"word_count":546,"visible_label_count":10,"question_count":7,"distractor_label_count":3,"why_this_level":"C1 level is achieved through a high word count (527 words), 10 visible labels with 3 distractors (C, G, I), dense spatial information, natural spoken style, self-corrections and elaboration that learners must filter, and indirect descriptions requiring spatial inference.","distractors":[{"label":"C","distractor_type":"mentioned location that is not a question target","transcript_evidence":"That block is actually used for storing cleaning chemicals and groundskeeping supplies — it's not a member facility, so please don't go in there."},{"label":"G","distractor_type":"position near the central path between Club House and Court 2 — block mentioned as non-member storage facility","transcript_evidence":"you'll pass a small block on your right-hand side, roughly level with Court 2. That block is actually used for storing cleaning chemicals and groundskeeping supplies"},{"label":"I","distractor_type":"unlabelled south-east area near Court 6 — never described in transcript","transcript_evidence":"Not referenced in transcript — pure visual distractor."}],"key_phrases":["the car parking area is located to the south-west of the site, just before you reach the Main Entrance","on your left — that's the western side as you wal