n the top right corner, beyond the pool. Area D is on the left side of the path near the entrance. All four labelled areas must appear as plain neutral shapes with no icons, furniture, signs, symbols, tools, products, pictograms, or decorative clues. Do not print any place names on or near the labelled areas. Only the words 'Entrance' and 'Pool' may appear as landmark text. The style should be simple and flat, suitable for a language test. No decorative clutter.","difficulty_notes":{"word_count":157,"visible_label_count":4,"question_count":4,"distractor_label_count":0,"why_this_level":"A2 level. 157 words, within the 120-180 word range. Four visible labels A, B, C, D with no distractors. Simple direction phrases used: on your left, on your right, near the entrance, at the top left, at the top right. Common vocabulary throughout. Each location is described directly and clearly.","distractors":[],"key_phrases":["on your left, just next to the entrance","on your right, also near the entrance","at the top left of the area","at the top right of the area, on the other side of the pool"],"visual_fairness_check":{"can_learners_guess_answers_from_image_alone":false,"anti_leak_checked":true,"notes":"All four labelled areas are visually neutral shapes. The pool and entrance are the only landmarks with visible text. No icons, furniture, signs, or symbols are used near labelled areas. Answers can only be identified by listening to the transcript."}}},"map_image":null,"thumbnail":null}	\N	\N
739	986	listening_tests	c6dbf474-6cd2-4edf-97ac-e76ea1649cee	{"status":"draft","title":"Stadium Surroundings Visitor Guide","slug":"stadium-surroundings-visitor-guide","description":"A bird's-eye map of the area surrounding a large football stadium. The stadium building sits at the centre. A main entrance gate is on the south side. Paths run around all four sides of the stadium. Six labelled locations (A to F) are positioned at neutral areas around the perimeter. Fixed landmarks include the stadium itself and the main entrance gate on the south side.","type":"map_labelling","level":"B1","accent":"British English","duration_seconds":null,"question_count":5,"is_free":true,"instruction_text":"Label the map below. Write the correct letter, A-F, next to Questions 1-5.","transcript":"Welcome to Riverside Stadium. Before kick-off, I'd like to give you a quick guide to the facilities around the ground so you know exactly where everything is.\\n\\nWhen you come through the Main Entrance on the south side, the path splits in two directions. If you head left along the south-west path, you will find our first aid point just past the corner. It is the first facility you reach on that side, so it is easy to locate if you or anyone in your group needs assistance.\\n\\nOn the opposite side of the entrance — so heading right from the Main Entrance towards the south-east corner — you will come across our club shop. It is right at that south-east corner, so you will not miss it on your way in.\\n\\nIf you continue further and walk along the west side of the stadium, you will find a refreshment kiosk about halfway up that path. Please note that there is also a recycling point at the far north-west corner of the ground, but that is not a visitor facility — it is for staff use only.\\n\\nFor those arriving by car, the car park is on the north side of the stadium, to the east of centre. Please follow the signs from the north path.\\n\\nFinally, the family toilets are situated on the east side, roughly halfway along that path. They are clearly marked with a letter on the map you have been given.","prosody_script":null,"questions_public_json":{"groups":[{"id":"g1","type":"map_labelling","title":"Questions 1-5","instruction":"Label the map below. Write the correct letter, A-F, next to Questions 1-5.","question_range":{"from":1,"to":5},"media":{"image":{"type":"image","field":"image_file"},"audio":{"type":"audio","field":"audio_file"}},"options":{"type":"letters","values":["A","B","C","D","E","F"]},"questions":[{"id":"q1","number":1,"text":"First Aid Point","input_type":"select","score":1},{"id":"q2","number":2,"text":"Club Shop","input_type":"select","score":1},{"id":"q3","number":3,"text":"Refreshment Kiosk","input_type":"select","score":1},{"id":"q4","number":4,"text":"Car Park","input_type":"select","score":1},{"id":"q5","number":5,"text":"Family Toilets","input_type":"select","score":1}]}]},"questions_answer_json":[{"id":"q1","correct_answer":"A","acceptable_answers":["A"],"score":1,"explanation":"The first aid point is located in the south-west corner, just past the corner when you head left from the Main Entrance. This matches label A on the map.","transcript_evidence":"If you head left along the south-west path, you will find our first aid point just past the corner."},{"id":"q2","correct_answer":"B","acceptable_answers":["B"],"score":1,"explanation":"The club shop is at the south-east corner, reached by heading right from the Main Entrance. This matches label B on the map.","transcript_evidence":"On the opposite side of the entrance — so heading right from the Main Entrance towards the south-east corner — you will come across our club shop. It is right at that south-east corner."},{"id":"q3","correct_answer":"C","acceptable_answers":["C"],"score":1,"explanation":"The refreshment kiosk is on the west side of the stadium, approximately halfway along the path. This matches label C on the map.","transcript_evidence":"If you continue further and walk along the west side of the stadium, you will find a refreshment kiosk about halfway up that path."},{"id":"q4","correct_answer":"E","acceptable_answers":["E"],"score":1,"explanation":"The car park is on the north side of the stadium, positioned to the east of centre. This matches label E on the map.","transcript_evidence":"For those arriving by car, the car park is on the north side of the stadium, to the east of centre."},{"id":"q5","correct_answer":"F","acceptable_answers":["F"],"score":1,"explanation":"The family toilets are on the east side of the stadium, roughly halfway along that path. This matches label F on the map.","transcript_evidence":"The family toilets are situated on the east side, roughly halfway along that path."}],"metadata":{"schema_version":"visual_labelling_listening_v1","topic":"Stadium Surroundings","speaker_role":"Stadium steward giving a pre-match visitor orientation","image_generation_prompt":"Create a clean bird's-eye outdoor map of the surroundings of a large football stadium. The stadium is a large rectangular building block positioned at the centre of the map. Label the stadium block with the text STADIUM. On the south face of the stadium, mark a gate with the text Main Entrance. Draw paths running along all four sides of the stadium perimeter. Place six letter labels — A, B, C, D, E, F — at the following positions: label A at a small neutral rectangular area in the south-west corner near the main entrance path; label B at a small neutral rectangular area in the south-east corner near the main entrance path; label C at a small neutral rectangular area on the west side path, mid-way along; label D at a small neutral rectangular area at the north-west corner; label E at a larger neutral rectangular area on the north side, east of centre; label F at a small neutral rectangular area on the east side path, mid-way along. All six labelled areas must appear as plain neutral shapes with no icons, signs, symbols, pictograms, furniture, tools, vehicles, products, or visual clues that suggest their function. Do not print any place names other than STADIUM and Main Entrance. Do not draw bicycles, medical crosses, shopping bags, food, cups, cars, parking symbols, restroom icons, or any other category-specific objects. The map style should be simple, flat, and clear, suitable for a listening test.","difficulty_notes":{"word_count":236,"visible_label_count":6,"question_count":5,"distractor_label_count":1,"why_this_level":"B1: 236 words, 6 labels (A-F), 5 questions, 1 distractor label (D = recycling point, mentioned as staff-only to misdirect). Multi-step directions used. Phrases include: just past the corner, on the opposite side, continue further, halfway up that path, to the east of centre, roughly halfway along.","distractors":["Label D (recycling point) is mentioned in the transcript but identified as a staff-only facility, not a visitor answer target. Learners must listen carefully to distinguish it from the five correct answer locations."],"key_phrases":["just past the corner","on the opposite side of the entrance","continue further and walk along the west side","halfway up that path","to the east of centre","on the east side, roughly halfway along that path"],"visual_fairness_check":{"can_learners_guess_answers_from_image_alone":false,"anti_leak_checked":true,"notes":"All six labelled areas are plain neutral shapes. No icons, signs, symbols, pictograms, vehicles, or objects appear on the labelled areas. The only printed text on the map is STADIUM and Main Entrance, both of which are fixed orientation landmarks. No answer can be inferred visually."}}},"map_image":null,"thumbnail":null}	{"status":"draft","title":"Stadium Surroundings Visitor Guide","slug":"stadium-surroundings-visitor-guide","description":"A bird's-eye map of the area surrounding a large football stadium. The stadium building sits at the centre. A main entrance gate is on the south side. Paths run around all four sides of the stadium. Si