740	987	listening_tests	ee6c4d93-ba0a-4fcf-90f9-29a19f9a82ff	{"status":"draft","title":"Sports Complex Grounds Tour","slug":"sports-complex-grounds-tour","description":"An outdoor map of a sports complex showing a main entrance at the south, a central path running north to south through the grounds, a north gate at the top, and eight labelled areas or buildings distributed across the site.","type":"map_labelling","level":"B2","accent":"British English","duration_seconds":null,"question_count":6,"is_free":true,"instruction_text":"Label the map below. Write the correct letter, A-H, next to Questions 1-6.","transcript":"Welcome to the Northfield Sports Complex. I am the facilities coordinator, and I am going to take you through the layout of the grounds so you know exactly where everything is.\\n\\nAs you come through the Main Entrance at the south end, you will notice two areas on either side of you. On your left, just inside the entrance, is where you can get changed before your session. On the right as you walk in, there used to be a reception office, but that has been relocated to the main building near the centre of the site. What you now find on the right, just inside the entrance, is the car park office, where staff manage vehicle access and issue permits.\\n\\nIf you continue north along the Central Path and look to your left roughly halfway along, you will come across the area for hiring equipment. This is a popular stop for visitors who have not brought their own kit. Directly opposite, on the right side of the path at the same point, is a maintenance block used by the groundskeeping team. This area is not open to the public.\\n\\nFurther along on the left-hand side, before you reach the North Gate, is the spectator seating area. This looks out over the main activity zone. On the opposite side of the grounds at mid-level, to the right, is a storage facility. Please note that access to the storage facility is restricted to authorised personnel only, so visitors should not attempt to enter.\\n\\nNow, up near the North Gate itself, there are two further areas. On the far left as you face the gate is where you can get refreshments. There were plans to move this to the centre of the complex, but in the end it remained in the top-left corner. On the far right, just before the North Gate, is where you will find the first aid point, which is staffed during all opening hours.","prosody_script":null,"questions_public_json":{"groups":[{"id":"g1","type":"map_labelling","title":"Questions 1-6","instruction":"Label the map below. Write the correct letter, A-H, next to Questions 1-6.","question_range":{"from":1,"to":6},"media":{"image":{"type":"image","field":"image_file"},"audio":{"type":"audio","field":"audio_file"}},"options":{"type":"letters","values":["A","B","C","D","E","F","G","H"]},"questions":[{"id":"q1","number":1,"text":"Changing Rooms","input_type":"select","score":1},{"id":"q2","number":2,"text":"Car Park Office","input_type":"select","score":1},{"id":"q3","number":3,"text":"Equipment Hire","input_type":"select","score":1},{"id":"q4","number":4,"text":"Spectator Seating","input_type":"select","score":1},{"id":"q5","number":5,"text":"Outdoor Cafe","input_type":"select","score":1},{"id":"q6","number":6,"text":"First Aid Point","input_type":"select","score":1}]}]},"questions_answer_json":[{"id":"q1","correct_answer":"A","acceptable_answers":["A"],"score":1,"explanation":"The changing rooms are located in the lower-left area, just inside the Main Entrance on the left-hand side, which corresponds to label A.","transcript_evidence":"On your left, just inside the entrance, is where you can get changed before your session."},{"id":"q2","correct_answer":"B","acceptable_answers":["B"],"score":1,"explanation":"The car park office is in the lower-right area, just inside the Main Entrance on the right-hand side, which corresponds to label B. The transcript explains the previous use (reception office) has moved and that the car park of