outh at the bottom and north at the top. Draw a clearly labelled 'Main Entrance' at the bottom centre. Draw a straight vertical path labelled 'Central Path' running from the Main Entrance at the bottom to a 'North Gate' at the top centre. All eight labelled areas must appear as plain, neutral rectangles or blocks only — no icons, no signs, no pictograms, no furniture, no equipment, no sports-related objects, no symbols, and no text that reveals their function. Place letter labels as follows: Label A is a neutral block in the lower-left area just inside the Main Entrance, to the left of the Central Path. Label B is a neutral block in the lower-right area just inside the Main Entrance, to the right of the Central Path. Label C is a neutral block on the left side of the map at mid-level. Label D is a neutral block on the right side of the map at mid-level. Label E is a neutral block at the top-left corner near the North Gate. Label F is a neutral block at the top-right corner near the North Gate. Label G is a neutral block on the left side of the Central Path just below mid-level. Label H is a neutral block on the right side of the Central Path at mid-level, directly opposite Label G. Only the fixed orientation landmarks — Main Entrance, Central Path, and North Gate — may have visible text. All labelled blocks must be visually identical and show only their letter. Do not add decorative clutter, sports courts, fields, trees, benches, or any other objects that could help learners identify the function of any labelled area.","difficulty_notes":{"word_count":319,"visible_label_count":8,"question_count":6,"distractor_label_count":2,"why_this_level":"B2 is appropriate because the transcript contains 319 words, 8 visible labels, 6 questions, and 2 distractor labels. The transcript uses changed location information (the reception office has moved), negation and restriction language (not open to the public, access restricted), and multi-step spatial directions. Distractors include a relocated reception office, a maintenance block opposite the equipment hire area, and a storage facility on the right at mid-level.","distractors":["The reception office is mentioned as a former use of the lower-right area, but the correct answer for that location is now the car park office.","The maintenance block at mid-level right is described as not open to the public — label H is the distractor for that position.","The storage facility on the right at mid-level is mentioned but is not a question target — label D is the distractor for that position. The plans to move the refreshments area to the centre are introduced and then negated."],"key_phrases":["just inside the entrance","used to be a reception office, but that has been relocated","on the left roughly halfway along","directly opposite","not open to the public","before you reach the North Gate","on the far left as you face the gate","on the far right, just before the North Gate"],"visual_fairness_check":{"can_learners_guess_answers_from_image_alone":false,"anti_leak_checked":true,"notes":"All eight labelled areas appear as plain neutral blocks with no icons, signs, furniture, equipment, or symbols. Only the fixed orientation landmarks — Main Entrance, Central Path, and North Gate — have visible text. No correct answer name or distractor function is revealed visually."}}},"map_image":null,"thumbnail":null}	{"status":"draft","title":"Sports Complex Grounds Tour","slug":"sports-complex-grounds-tour","description":"An outdoor map of a sports complex showing a main entrance at the south, a central path running north to south through the grounds, a north gate at the top, and eight labelled areas or buildings distributed across the site.","type":"map_labelling","level":"B2","accent":"British English","duration_seconds":null,"question_count":6,"is_free":true,"instruction_text":"Label the map below. Write the correct letter, A-H, next to Questions 1-6.","transcript":"Welcome to the Northfield Sports Complex. 