_version":"visual_labelling_listening_v1","topic":"Golf Course Map","speaker_role":"golf course staff member giving a welcome tour","image_generation_prompt":"Create a clean, flat-style outdoor golf course map in landscape orientation. The map has three fixed orientation landmarks with printed text: 'Main Entrance' at the bottom centre, 'Car Park' at the bottom left, and 'Clubhouse' at the top centre. A main path runs from the Main Entrance northward to the Clubhouse. A side path branches east from the main path near the centre of the map. Place six letter labels on the map as follows: label A is a neutral rectangular area at the bottom right near the Main Entrance on the east side; label B is a neutral rectangular area on the left side midway up the map beside the main path; label C is a neutral area in the centre of the map just east of the main path; label D is a neutral rectangular area at the top left near the Clubhouse; label E is a neutral area at the top right at the far end of the side path; label F is a neutral area on the right side in the lower section south of label E. All six labelled locations must appear as plain neutral blocks or shapes with no icons, no symbols, no signs, no furniture, no vehicles, no tools, no products, no pictograms, and no text other than their letter label. The map should include simple grass areas, light path lines, and gentle landscape shading. Do not add any visual clue that reveals the function or purpose of any labelled location.","difficulty_notes":{"word_count":239,"visible_label_count":6,"question_count":5,"distractor_label_count":1,"why_this_level":"B1: 239 words, 5 questions, 6 labels (A-F), 1 distractor label (D - storage building), one light distractor in transcript (storage building mentioned but marked as not open to visitors), multi-step directions used, phrases such as just to the right, roughly halfway up, at the far end, just before, south of.","distractors":["Label D (storage building near the clubhouse) is mentioned in the transcript as not open to visitors, making it a plausible distractor for the pro shop question."],"key_phrases":["just to the right of the entrance","roughly halfway up","take the side path heading east","at the far end","just before you reach the side path turning","south of the refreshment kiosk"],"visual_fairness_check":{"can_learners_guess_answers_from_image_alone":false,"anti_leak_checked":true,"notes":"All six labelled areas are visually neutral blocks. No icons, symbols, or objects are used. Fixed orientation landmarks (Main Entrance, Clubhouse, Car Park) do not reveal any answer. Learners must listen to identify all five answers."}}},"map_image":null,"thumbnail":null}	\N	\N
742	989	listening_tests	6fffbc7c-f487-48f4-b3e2-d6c6cacec035	{"status":"draft","title":"Meadowbrook Dairy Farm Tour","slug":"meadowbrook-dairy-farm-tour","description":"A map of a dairy farm with paths, buildings, and an entrance.","type":"map_labelling","level":"B2","accent":"British English","duration_seconds":null,"question_count":6,"is_free":true,"instruction_text":"Label the map below. Write the correct letter, A-H, next to Questions 1-6.","transcript":"Welcome everyone to the Meadowbrook Dairy Farm. We are thrilled to have you here for our afternoon tour. Before we set off, please take a look at the maps I've just handed out so you can get your bearings. You'll see we are currently standing at the Main Entrance, which is at the bottom of your map.\\n\\nIf you look straight ahead from the entrance, along the main path on the left hand side, you'll see a large building. That is the Cheese Shop. We originally planned to put the farm museum there, but our cheese production expanded so much we needed the extra space for sales instead.\\n\\nContinuing up the main path, you'll notice it splits into two directions. If you follow the left branch, right at the very end of that path is the Milking Barn. We have a viewing gallery there where you can watch the afternoon milking session.\\n\\nNow, just opposite the Milking Barn, across the path on the right hand side, is a smaller structure. That's the Calf Shed. We've got several newborn calves in there at the moment, which are always very popular with our visitors.\\n\\nLet's go back to where the main path split. If you take the right branch this time, you'll soon reach a corner. Just beyond this corner, on the right hand side of the path, is our Farm Museum. It houses some fascinating historical farming equipment. You might also notice another building marked on the far right of the map, just before you reach the museum. That used to be the old tractor shed, but it's currently closed for renovations, so please don't try to go in there.\\n\\nMoving past the museum, the path continues towards the top right of the map. At the very end of this path is the Pasture Gate. We'll be heading there later to see the main herd grazing in the fields.\\n\\nFinally, if you're looking for somewhere to eat your lunch, we have a lovely Picnic Area. From the main entrance, if you look to your immediate right, there's a short side path leading to a circular space. That's the picnic area. It's a great spot to relax. I should also point out that the area immediately to the left of the entrance is just staff parking, so please keep clear of that section.\\n\\nAlright, if everyone is ready, let's begin our tour...","prosody_script":null,"questions_public_json":{"groups":[{"id":"g1","type":"map_labelling","title":"Questions 1-6","instruction":"Label the map below. Write the correct letter, A-H, next to Questions 1-6.","question_range":{"from":1,"to":6},"media":{"image":{"type":"image","field":"image_file"},"audio":{"type":"audio","field":"audio_file"}},"options":{"type":"letters","values":["A","B","C","D","E","F","G","H"]},"questions":[{"id":"q1","number":1,"text":"Cheese Shop","input_type":"select","score":1},{"id":"q2","number":2,"text":"Milking Barn","input_type":"select","score":1},{"id":"q3","number":3,"text":"Calf Shed","input_type":"select","score":1},{"id":"q4","number":4,"text":"Farm Museum","input_type":"select","score":1},{"id":"q5","number":5,"text":"Pasture Gate","input_type":"select","score":1},{"id":"q6","number":6,"text":"Picnic Area","input_type":"select","score":1}]}]},"questions_answer_json":[{"id":"q1","correct_answer":"A","acceptable_answers":["A"],"score":1,"explanation":"The Cheese Shop is the large building along the main path on the left hand side.","transcript_evidence":"along the main path on the left hand side, you'll see a large building. That is the Cheese Shop."},{"id":"q2","correct_answer":"B","acceptable_answers":["B"],"score":1,"explanation":"The Milking Barn is at the very end of the left branch of the main path.","transcript_evidence":"If you follow the left branch, right at the very end of that path is the Milking Barn."},{"id":"q3","correct_answer":"C","acceptable_answers":["C"],"score":1,"explanation":"The Calf Shed is opposite the Milking Barn, across the path on the right hand side.","transcript_evidence":"just opposite the Milking Barn, across the path on the right hand side, is a smaller structure. That's the Calf Shed."},{"id":"q4","correct_answer":"D","acceptable_answers":["D"],"score":1,"explanation":"The Farm Museum is just beyond the corner on the right branch, on the right hand side of the path.","transcript_evidence":"take the right branch... Just beyond this corner, on the right hand side of the path, is our Farm Museum."},{"id":"q5","correct_answer":"F","acceptable_answers":["F"],"score":1,"explanation":"The Pasture Gate is at the very end of the path that continues towards the top right of the map.","transcript_evidence":"the path continues towards the top right of the map. At the very end of this path is the Pasture Gate."},{"id":"q6","correct_answer":"G","acceptable_answers":["G"],"score":1,"explanation":"The Picnic Area is a circular space down a short side path to the immediate right of the main entrance.","transcript_evidence":"From the main entrance, if you look to your immediate right, there's a short side path leading to a circular space. That's the picnic area."}],"metadata":{"schema_version":"visual_labelling_listening_v1","topic":"Dairy Farm","speaker_role":"Tour Guide","image_generation_prompt":"An outdoor map layout of a dairy farm. At the bottom center, there is a fixed text label 'Main Entrance'. A main path leads north from the entrance and splits into a left branch and a right branch. Provide visible letter labels A to H in the following neutral locations: Label A is a building shape along the left side of the main path. Label B is at the far end of the left branch. Label C is a building shape oppos