743	990	listening_tests	15c782fd-9623-46ce-9d4d-727eaf262d8f	{"id":"15c782fd-9623-46ce-9d4d-727eaf262d8f","title":"Tennis Club Grounds Tour","slug":"tennis-club-grounds-tour","description":"A bird's-eye map of a tennis club showing the full grounds including courts, pathways, a central club house, and various ancillary facilities arranged around the site. Ten neutral areas or buildings are labelled A through J. Only fixed orientation landmarks such as the Main Entrance, the Club House, and the numbered courts are visually identifiable. All other labelled locations appear as plain neutral blocks or areas.","accent":"British English","duration_seconds":null,"question_count":7,"is_free":true,"instruction_text":"Label the map below. Write the correct letter, A-J, next to Questions 1-7.","transcript":"Welcome to Greenfield Tennis Club. My name is Sandra, and I'm the club administrator. I'll be taking you on a quick orientation of the grounds so that you know where everything is before your first session. We have quite a lot to cover, so do listen carefully.\\n\\nIf you're arriving by car, you'll want to note that the car parking area is located to the south-west of the site, just before you reach the Main Entrance. It's a generous open area and usually has plenty of space on weekday mornings. From there, you walk east along the perimeter path until you reach the Main Entrance gates.\\n\\nAs you come through the Main Entrance, the first thing you'll notice on your left — that's the western side as you walk in — is our equipment and apparel outlet. We stock rackets, balls, grips, and branded clothing. Players often pop in before a match to pick something up. That facility is on the left as you enter.\\n\\nOn your right as you come through the gate — so the eastern side — are the changing rooms. We have separate facilities for men and women, and there are secure lockers available. I'd encourage all new members to use the lockers rather than leaving valuables in bags at courtside.\\n\\nNow, if you walk north along the central path towards the Club House, you'll pass a small block on your right-hand side, roughly level with Court 2. That block is actually used for storing cleaning chemicals and groundskeeping supplies — it's not a member facility, so please don't go in there. Continuing past that, you reach the Club House itself.\\n\\nOn the eastern side of the Club House — right beside it to the north-east — we have a small room that is staffed during all opening hours by a qualified first-aider. This is an important facility and we're rather proud that we have it available every single day we're open. Please make a note of where it is.\\n\\nIf you head around to the back of the Club House — directly north — you'll find the office belonging to our head groundskeeper, Marcus. He manages court maintenance, oversees the irrigation schedule, and coordinates the volunteers who prepare the courts each morning. His office is tucked directly behind the Club House against the back fence, and he's always happy to take questions about court conditions.\\n\\nMoving over to the eastern courts, between Courts 4 and 5, right up against the east perimeter fence, we have a dedicated area for watching match play. This is particularly busy during our weekend tournaments and the annual club championship. It's a popular spot, so arrive early if you want a good view during competitive events.\\n\\nFinally, I want to tell you about our coaching facility. We run a full junior and adult coaching programme here at Greenfield, and the dedicated coaching space is in the north-west corner of the grounds, right next to Court 1. It has its own entrance from the western perimeter path. The lead coach, Rachel, runs sessions on Tuesday and Thursday evenings as well as Saturday mornings.\\n\\nThat covers the main areas. Please feel free to walk around and get your bearings before the induction session begins at half past two.","prosody_script":null,"date_created":"2026-06-18T14:53:46.415Z","date_updated":"2026-06-18T14:53:46.415Z","status":"published","metadata":{"schema_version":"visual_labelling_listening_v1","topic":"Tennis Club Grounds","speaker_role":"Club Administrator giving a guided orientation for new members","image_generation_prompt":"Create a clean bird's-eye map illustration of a tennis club grounds. The site is rectangular and enclosed by a perimeter fence. The Main Entrance is at the bottom-centre (south edge) — label it 'Main Entrance'. A wide central path leads from the entrance north to the Club House in the upper-centre of the map — label it 'Club House'. On the west side of the site, three rectangular tennis courts are arranged vertically: label them 'Court 1' (upper west), 'Court 2' (middle west), 'Court 3' (lower west). On the east side, three rectangular tennis courts are arranged vertically: label them 'Court 4' (upper east), 'Court 5' (middle east), 'Court 6' (lower east). Place ten neutral rectangular blocks or areas labelled A through J as follows: A — south-west corner, immediately left of the Main Entrance as you enter; B — south-east corner, immediately right of the Main Entrance as you enter; C — west side, below Court 3 near the south-west perimeter; D — east side, between Court 4 and Court 5 against the eastern fence; E — north-west corner, beside Court 1 against the northern fence; F — south side, west of the Main Entrance in the south-west as an open area; G — centre of the site, just north of the central path between the Club House and Court 2; H — north-east corner, beside the Club House on the east side; I — east side, south of Court 6 near the south-east perimeter; J — north side, directly behind the Club House against the northern perimeter fence. All labelled blocks and areas must be visually neutral plain shapes with only the letter label visible. Do not draw icons, signs, logos, pictograms, furniture, vehicles, tools, equipment, symbols, or any objects that suggest the function of any labelled location. Do not print any place names other than 'Main Entrance', 'Club House', 'Court 1', 'Court 2', 'Court 3', 'Court 4', 'Court 5', and 'Court 6' on the image. Learners must not be able to identify any labelled location without listening to the audio.","difficulty_notes":{"word_count":546,"visible_label_count":10,"question_count":7,"distractor_label_count":3,"why_this_level":"C1 level is achieved through a high word count (527 words), 10 visible labels with 3 distractors (C, G, I), dense spatial information, natural spoken style, self-corrections and elaboration that learners must filter, and indirect descriptions requiring spatial inference.","distractors":[{"label":"C","distractor_type":"mentioned location that is not a question target","transcript_evidence":"That block is actually used for storing cleaning chemicals and groundskeeping supplies — it's not a member facility, so please don't go in there."},{"label":"G","distractor_type":"position near the central path between Club House and Court 2 — block mentioned as non-member storage facility","transcript_evidence":"you'll pass a small block on your right-hand side, roughly level with Court 2. That block is actually used for storing cleaning chemicals and groundskeeping supplies"},{"label":"I","distractor_type":"unlabelled south-east area near Court 6 — never described in transcript","transcript_evidence":"Not referenced in transcript — pure visual distractor."}],"key_phrases":["the car parking area is located to the south-west of the site, just before you reach the Main Entrance","on your left — that's the western side as you walk in — is our equipment and apparel outlet","On your right as you come through the gate — so the eastern side — are the changing rooms","On the eastern side of the Club House — right beside it to the north-east — we have a small room that is staffed during all opening hours by a qualified first-aider","directly behind the Club House against the back fence","between Courts 4 and 5, right up against the east perimeter fence, we have a dedicated area for watching match play","the dedicated coaching space is in the north-west corner of the grounds, right next to Court 1"],"visual_fairness_check":{"can_learners_guess_answers_from_image_alone":false,"anti_leak_checked":true,"notes":"All ten labelled locations appear as plain neutral blocks or open areas. No icons, signs, symbols, furniture, vehicles, or pictograms are included. Only fixed landmarks (Main Entrance, Club House, Courts 1-6) are visually identifiable. Every question target and all distractor labels are visually identical neutral shapes distinguishable only by their letter label and spatial position."}}},"questions_public_json":{"groups":[{"id":"g1","type":"map_labelling","title":"Questions 1-7","instruction":"Label the map below. Write the correct letter, A-J, next to Questions 1-7.","question_range":{"from":1,"to":7},"media":{"image":{"type":"image","field":"image_file"},"audio":{"type":"audio","field":"audio_file"}},"options":{"type":"letters","values":["A","B","C","D","E","F","G","H","I","J"]},"questions":[{"id":"q1","number":1,"text":"Car Park","input_type":"select","score":1},{"id":"q2","number":2,"text":"Pro Shop","input_type":"select","score":1},{"id":"q3","number":3,"text":"Changing Rooms","input_type":"select","score":1},{"id":"q4","number":4,"text":"First Aid Room","input_type":"select","score":1},{"id":"q5","number":5,"text":"Groundskeeper's Office","input_type":"select","score":1},{"id":"q6","number":6,"text":"Spectator Seating","input_type":"select","score":1},{"id":"q7","number":7,"text":"Coaching Academy","input_type":"select","score":1}]}]},"questions_answer_json":[{"id":"q1","correct_answer":"F","acceptable_answers":["F"],"score":1,"explanation":"The car parking area is in the south-west of the site, west of the Main Entrance, described as a generous open area reached before entering through the Main Entrance gates. This matches label F, which is positioned to the south-west outside the main courts area.","transcript_evidence":"the car parking area is located to the south-west of the site, just before you reach the Main Entrance. It's a generous open area and usually has plenty of space on weekday mornings."},{"id":"q2","correct_answer":"A","acceptable_answers":["A"],"score":1,"explanation":"The pro shop (described as the equipment and apparel outlet) is on the left as you enter through the Main Entrance, which is the western side. This corresponds to label A in the south-west corner beside the entrance on the left.","transcript_evidence":"the first thing you'll notice on your left — that's the western side as you walk in — is our equipment and apparel outlet. We stock rackets, balls, grips, and branded clothing."},{"id":"q3","correct_answer":"B","acceptable_answers":["B"],"score":1,"explanation":"The changing rooms are on the right as you come through the Main Entrance gate, meaning the eastern side. This corresponds to label B in the south-east corner beside the entrance on the right.","transcript_evidence":"On your right as you come through the gate — so the eastern side — are the changing rooms. We have separate facilities for men and women, and there are secure lockers available."},{"id":"q4","correct_answer":"H","acceptable_answers":["H"],"score":1,"explanation":"The first aid room is described as being on the eastern side of the Club House, directly beside it to the north-east. This matches label H positioned in the north-east corner beside the Club House.","transcript_evidence":"On the eastern side of the Club House — right beside it to the north-east — we have a small room that is staffed during all opening hours by a qualified first-aider."},{"id":"q5","correct_answer":"J","acceptable_answers":["J"],"score":1,"explanation":"The groundskeeper's office is located directly behind the Club House against the back (northern) fence. This matches label J, which is positioned on the north side directly behind the Club House against the northern perimeter fence.","transcript_evidence":"His office is tucked directly behind the Club House against the back fence, and he's always happy to take questions about court conditions."},{"id":"q6","correct_answer":"D","acceptable_answers":["D"],"score":1,"explanation":"The spectator seating area is described as being between Courts 4 and 5, right up against the east perimeter fence. This matches label D, positioned on the east side between Court 4 and Court 5 against the eastern perimeter fence.","transcript_evidence":"between Courts 4 and 5, right up against the east perimeter fence, we have a dedicated area for watching match play."},{"id":"q7","correct_answer":"E","acceptable_answers":["E"],"score":1,"explanation":"The coaching academy (described as the dedicated coaching space) is in the north-west corner of the grounds, right next to Court 1. This matches label E, which is positioned in the north-west corner beside Court 1 against the northern perimeter.","transcript_evidence":"the dedicated coaching space is in the north-west corner of the grounds, right next to Court 1. It has its own entrance from the western perimeter path."}],"thumbnail":null,"map_image":null,"type":"map_labelling","topic":null,"tests_taken":"0","level":"C1","audio_file":[]}	{"status":"published"}	\N	\N
744	991	listening_tests	6fffbc7c-f487-48f4-b3e2-d6c6cacec035	{"id":"6fffbc7c-f487-48f4-b3e2-d6c6cacec035","title":"Meadowbrook Dairy Farm Tour","slug":"meadowbrook-dairy-farm-tour","description":"A map of a dairy farm with paths, buildings, and an entrance.","accent":"British English","duration_seconds":null,"question_count":6,"is_free":true,"instruction_text":"Label the map below. Write the correct letter, A-H, next to Questions 1-6.","transcript":"Welcome everyone to the Meadowbrook Dairy Farm. We are thrilled to have you here for our afternoon tour. Before we set off, please take a look at the maps I've just handed out so you can get your bearings. You'll see we are currently standing at the Main Entrance, which is at the bottom of your map.\\n\\nIf you look straight ahead from the entrance, along the main path on the left hand side, you'll see a large building. That is the Cheese Shop. We originally planned to put the farm museum there, but our cheese production expanded so much we needed the extra space for sales instead.\\n\\nContinuing up the main path, you'll notice it splits into two directions. If you follow the left branch, right at the very end of that path is the Milking Barn. We have a viewing gallery there where you can watch the afternoon milking session.\\n\\nNow, just opposite the Milking Barn, across the path on the right hand side, is a smaller structure. That's the Calf Shed. We've got several newborn calves in there at the moment, which are always very popular with our visitors.\\n\\nLet's go back to where the main path split. If you take the right branch this time, you'll soon reach a corner. Just beyond this corner, on the right hand side of the path, is our Farm Museum. It houses some fascinating historical farming equipment. You might also notice another building marked on the far right of the map, just before you reach the museum. That used to be the old tractor shed, but it's currently closed for renovations, so please don't try to go in there.\\n\\nMoving past the museum, the path continues towards the top right of the map. At the very end of this path is the Pasture Gate. We'll be heading there later to see the main herd grazing in the fields.\\n\\nFinally, if you're looking for somewhere to eat your lunch, we have a lovely Picnic Area. From the main entrance, if you look to your immediate right, there's a short side path leading to a circular space. That's the picnic area. It's a great spot to relax. I should also point out that the area immediately to the left of the entrance is just staff parking, so please keep clear of that section.\\n\\nAlright, if everyone is ready, let's begin our tour...","prosody_script":null,"date_created":"2026-06-18T14:54:52.590Z","date_updated":"2026-06-18T14:54:52.590Z","status":"published","metadata":{"schema_version":"visual_labelling_listening_v1","topic":"Dairy Farm","speaker_role":"Tour Guide","image_generation_prompt":"An outdoor map layout of a dairy farm. At the bottom center, there is a fixed text label 'Main Entrance'. A main path leads north from the entrance and splits into a left branch and a right branch. Provide visible letter labels A to H in the following neutral locations: Label A is a building shape along the left side of the main path. Label B is at the far end of the left branch. Label C is a building shape opposite Label B, on the right side of the left branch. Label D is a building shape past a corner on the right branch, located on the right side of the path. Label E is a shape on the far right of the map, positioned before reaching Label D. Label F is a shape at the very end of the right path towards the top right. Label G is a circular space down a short side path to the immediate right of the main entrance. Label H is a shape immediately to the left of the main entrance. All labeled locations must be visually neutral shapes (e.g., plain buildings or areas). Do not draw any icons, cows, cheese, tractors, picnic tables, cars, signs, or products that reveal the functions of the locations. The map should be clean and clear.","difficulty_notes":{"word_count":400,"visible_label_count":8,"question_count":6,"distractor_label_count":2,"why_this_level":"Includes multi-step directions, changed locations (museum to cheese shop), negations (closed for renovations), and natural distractors.","distractors":["farm museum originally planned for cheese shop location","old tractor shed","staff parking"],"key_phrases":["straight ahead","splits into two directions","opposite","just beyond this corner","far right","immediate right"],"visual_fairness_check":{"can_learners_guess_answers_from_image_alone":false,"anti_leak_checked":true,"notes":"All answer locations are described as neutral shapes in the prompt."}}},"questions_public_json":{"groups":[{"id":"g1","type":"map_labelling","title":"Questions 1-6","instruction":"Label the map below. Write the correct letter, A-H, next to Questions 1-6.","question_range":{"from":1,"to":6},"media":{"image":{"type":"image","field":"image_file"},"audio":{"type":"audio","field":"audio_file"}},"options":{"type":"letters","values":["A","B","C","D","E","F","G","H"]},"questions":[{"id":"q1","number":1,"text":"Cheese Shop","input_type":"select","score":1},{"id":"q2","number":2,"text":"Milking Barn","input_type":"select","score":1},{"id":"q3","number":3,"text":"Calf Shed","input_type":"select","score":1},{"id":"q4","number":4,"text":"Farm Museum","input_type":"select","score":1},{"id":"q5","number":5,"text":"Pasture Gate","input_type":"select","score":1},{"id":"q6","number":6,"text":"Picnic Area","input_type":"select","score":1}]}]},"questions_answer_json":[{"id":"q1","correct_answer":"A","acceptable_answers":["A"],"score":1,"explanation":"The Cheese Shop is the large building along the main path on the left hand side.","transcript_evidence":"along the main path on the left hand side, you'll see a large building. That is the Cheese Shop."},{"id":"q2","correct_answer":"B","acceptable_answers":["B"],"score":1,"explanation":"The Milking Barn is at the very end of the left branch of the main path.","transcript_evidence":"If you follow the left branch, right at the very end of that path is the Milking Barn."},{"id":"q3","correct_answer":"C","acceptable_answers":["C"],"score":1,"explanation":"The Calf Shed is opposite the Milking Barn, across the path on the right hand side.","transcript_evidence":"just opposite the Milking Barn, across the path on the right hand side, is a smaller structure. That's the Calf Shed."},{"id":"q4","correct_answer":"D","acceptable_answers":["D"],"score":1,"explanation":"The Farm Museum is just beyond the corner on the right branch, on the right hand side of the path.","transcript_evidence":"take the right branch... Just beyond this corner, on the right hand side of the path, is our Farm Museum."},{"id":"q5","correct_answer":"F","acceptable_answers":["F"],"score":1,"explanation":"The Pasture Gate is at the very end of the path that continues towards the top right of the map.","transcript_evidence":"the path continues towards the top right of the map. At the very end of this path is the Pasture Gate."},{"id":"q6","correct_answer":"G","acceptable_answers":["G"],"score":1,"explanation":"The Picnic Area is a circular space down a short side path to the immediate right of the main entrance.","transcript_evidence":"From the main entrance, if you look to your immediate right, there's a short side path leading to a circular space. That's the picnic area."}],"thumbnail":null,"map_image":null,"type":"map_labelling","topic":null,"tests_taken":"0","level":"B2","audio_file":[]}	{"status":"published"}	\N	\N
745	992	listening_tests	ab5c957c-bdd2-4098-b900-7eedfbd56fe3	{"id":"ab5c957c-bdd2-4098-b900-7eedfbd56fe3","title":"Swimming Centre Outdoor Area","slug":"swimming-centre-outdoor-area","description":"A top-down map of the outdoor area of a swimming centre. The main entrance is at the bottom centre. A central path runs from the entrance northward through the area. A large outdoor pool is in the centre of the map. There are four neutral areas labelled A, B, C, and D. Area A is in the top left corner, beyond the pool. Area B is to the right of the central path near the entrance. Area C is at the top right, beyond the pool. Area D is to the left of the central path near the entrance.","accent":"British English","duration_seconds":null,"question_count":4,"is_free":true,"instruction_text":"Label the map below. Write the correct letter, A-D, next to Questions 1-4.","transcript":"Welcome to the outdoor area of the swimming centre. I will tell you about the main facilities. When you come in through the entrance, you can see the large outdoor pool straight ahead of you. On your left, just next to the entrance, is our reception. You can buy tickets and get information there. On your right, also near the entrance, are the changing rooms. Please use these before you go to the pool. After your swim, if you are hungry or thirsty, walk along the path and go past the pool. At the top left of the area, you will find our seating area. This is a great place to relax. If you would like something to eat or drink, our refreshment kiosk is at the top right of the area, on the other side of the pool. We hope you enjoy your visit.","prosody_script":null,"date_created":"2026-06-18T14:54:05.838Z","date_updated":"2026-06-18T14:54:05.838Z","status":"published","metadata":{"schema_version":"visual_labelling_listening_v1","topic":"Swimming Centre Outdoor Area","speaker_role":"Swimming centre staff member giving a guided introduction to visitors","image_generation_prompt":"Create a clean, top-down outdoor map of a swimming centre. The map is rectangular. The main entrance is labelled 'Entrance' at the bottom centre. A straight central path runs from the entrance northward to the top of the map. A large rectangular pool labelled 'Pool' sits in the centre of the map. There are four neutral rectangular areas on the map, each marked with a single capital letter only. Area A is in the top left corner, beyond the pool. Area B is on the right side of the path near the entrance. Area C is in the top right corner, beyond the pool. Area D is on the left side of the path near the entrance. All four labelled areas must appear as plain neutral shapes with no icons, furniture, signs, symbols, tools, products, pictograms, or decorative clues. Do not print any place names on or near the labelled areas. Only the words 'Entrance' and 'Pool' may appear as landmark text. The style should be simple and flat, suitable for a language test. No decorative clutter.","difficulty_notes":{"word_count":157,"visible_label_count":4,"question_count":4,"distractor_label_count":0,"why_this_level":"A2 level. 157 words, within the 120-180 word range. Four visible labels A, B, C, D with no distractors. Simple direction phrases used: on your left, on your right, near the entrance, at the top left, at the top right. Common vocabulary throughout. Each location is described directly and clearly.","distractors":[],"key_phrases":["on your left, just next to the entrance","on your right, also near the entrance","at the top left of the area","at the top right of the area, on the other side of the pool"],"visual_fairness_check":{"can_learners_guess_answers_from_image_alone":false,"anti_leak_checked":true,"notes":"All four labelled areas are visually neutral shapes. The pool and entrance are the only landmarks with visible text. No icons, furniture, signs, or symbols are used near labelled areas. Answers can only be identified by listening to the transcript."}}},"questions_public_json":{"groups":[{"id":"g1","type":"map_labelling","title":"Questions 1-4","instruction":"Label the map below. Write the correct letter, A-D, next to Questions 1-4.","question_range":{"from":1,"to":4},"media":{"image":{"type":"image","field":"image_file"},"audio":{"type":"audio","field":"audio_file"}},"options":{"type":"letters","values":["A","B","C","D"]},"questions":[{"id":"q1","number":1,"text":"Reception","input_type":"select","score":1},{"id":"q2","number":2,"text":"Changing rooms","input_type":"select","score":1},{"id":"q3","number":3,"text":"Seating area","input_type":"select","score":1},{"id":"q4","number":4,"text":"Refreshment kiosk","input_type":"select","score":1}]}]},"questions_answer_json":[{"id":"q1","correct_answer":"D","acceptable_answers":["D"],"score":1,"explanation":"The reception is on the left side near the entrance, which corresponds to label D on the map.","transcript_evidence":"On your left, just next to the entrance, is our reception."},{"id":"q2","correct_answer":"B","acceptable_answers":["B"],"score":1,"explanation":"The changing rooms are on the right side near the entrance, which corresponds to label B on the map.","transcript_evidence":"On your right, also near the entrance, are the changing rooms."},{"id":"q3","correct_answer":"A","acceptable_answers":["A"],"score":1,"explanation":"The seating area is at the top left of the outdoor area, beyond the pool, which corresponds to label A on the map.","transcript_evidence":"At the top left of the area, you will find our seating area."},{"id":"q4","correct_answer":"C","acceptable_answers":["C"],"score":1,"explanation":"The refreshment kiosk is at the top right of the outdoor area, on the other side of the pool, which corresponds to label C on the map.","transcript_evidence":"Our refreshment kiosk is at the top right of the area, on the other side of the pool."}],"thumbnail":null,"map_image":null,"type":"map_labelling","topic":null,"tests_taken":"0","level":"A2","audio_file":[]}	{"status":"published"}	\N	\N
746	993	listening_tests	c6dbf474-6cd2-4edf-97ac-e76ea1649cee	{"id":"c6dbf474-6cd2-4edf-97ac-e76ea1649cee","title":"Stadium Surroundings Visitor Guide","slug":"stadium-surroundings-visitor-guide","description":"A bird's-eye map of the area surrounding a large football stadium. The stadium building sits at the centre. A main entrance gate is on the south side. Paths run around all four sides of the stadium. Six labelled locations (A to F) are positioned at neutral areas around the perimeter. Fixed landmarks include the stadium itself and the main entrance gate on the south side.","accent":"British English","duration_seconds":null,"question_count":5,"is_free":true,"instruction_text":"Label the map below. Write the correct letter, A-F, next to Questions 1-5.","transcript":"Welcome to Riverside Stadium. Before kick-off, I'd like to give you a quick guide to the facilities around the ground so you know exactly where everything is.\\n\\nWhen you come through the Main Entrance on the south side, the path splits in two directions. If you head left along the south-west path, you will find our first aid point just past the corner. It is the first facility you reach on that side, so it is easy to locate if you or anyone in your group needs assistance.\\n\\nOn the opposite side of the entrance — so heading right from the Main Entrance towards the south-east corner — you will come across our club shop. It is right at that south-east corner, so you will not miss it on your way in.\\n\\nIf you continue further and walk along the west side of the stadium, you will find a refreshment kiosk about halfway up that path. Please note that there is also a recycling point at the far north-west corner of the ground, but that is not a visitor facility — it is for staff use only.\\n\\nFor those arriving by car, the car park is on the north side of the stadium, to the east of centre. Please follow the signs from the north path.\\n\\nFinally, the family toilets are situated on the east side, roughly halfway along that path. They are clearly marked with a letter on the map you have been given.","prosody_script":null,"date_created":"2026-06-18T14:54:14.446Z","date_updated":"2026-06-18T14:54:14.446Z","status":"published","metadata":{"schema_version":"visual_labelling_listening_v1","topic":"Stadium Surroundings","speaker_role":"Stadium steward giving a pre-match visitor orientation","image_generation_prompt":"Create a clean bird's-eye outdoor map of the surroundings of a large football stadium. The stadium is a large rectangular building block positioned at the centre of the map. Label the stadium block with the text STADIUM. On the south face of the stadium, mark a gate with the text Main Entrance. Draw paths running along all four sides of the stadium perimeter. Place six letter labels — A, B, C, D, E, F — at the following positions: label A at a small neutral rectangular area in the south-west corner near the main entrance path; label B at a small neutral rectangular area in the south-east corner near the main entrance path; label C at a small neutral rectangular area on the west side path, mid-way along; label D at a small neutral rectangular area at the north-west corner; label E at a larger neutral rectangular area on the north side, east of centre; label F at a small neutral rectangular area on the east side path, mid-way along. All six labelled areas must appear as plain neutral shapes with no icons, signs, symbols, pictograms, furniture, tools, vehicles, products, or visual clues that suggest their function. Do not print any place names other than STADIUM and Main Entrance. Do not draw bicycles, medical crosses, shopping bags, food, cups, cars, parking symbols, restroom icons, or any other category-specific objects. The map style should be simple, flat, and clear, suitable for a listening test.","difficulty_notes":{"word_count":236,"visible_label_count":6,"question_count":5,"distractor_label_count":1,"why_this_level":"B1: 236 words, 6 labels (A-F), 5 questions, 1 distractor label (D = recycling point, mentioned as staff-only to misdirect). Multi-step directions used. Phrases include: just past the corner, on the opposite side, continue further, halfway up that path, to the east of centre, roughly halfway along.","distractors":["Label D (recycling point) is mentioned in the transcript but identified as a staff-only facility, not a visitor answer target. Learners must listen carefully to distinguish it from the five correct answer locations."],"key_phrases":["just past the corner","on the opposite side of the entrance","continue further and walk along the west side","halfway up that path","to the east of centre","on the east side, roughly halfway along that path"],"visual_fairness_check":{"can_learners_guess_answers_from_image_alone":false,"anti_leak_checked":true,"notes":"All six labelled areas are plain neutral shapes. No icons, signs, symbols, pictograms, vehicles, or objects appear on the labelled areas. The only printed text on the map is STADIUM and Main Entrance, both of which are fixed orientation landmarks. No answer can be inferred visually."}}},"questions_public_json":{"groups":[{"id":"g1","type":"map_labelling","title":"Questions 1-5","instruction":"Label the map below. Write the correct letter, A-F, next to Questions 1-5.","question_range":{"from":1,"to":5},"media":{"image":{"type":"image","field":"image_file"},"audio":{"type":"audio","field":"audio_file"}},"options":{"type":"letters","values":["A","B","C","D","E","F"]},"questions":[{"id":"q1","number":1,"text":"First Aid Point","input_type":"select","score":1},{"id":"q2","number":2,"text":"Club Shop","input_type":"select","score":1},{"id":"q3","number":3,"text":"Refreshment Kiosk","input_type":"select","score":1},{"id":"q4","number":4,"text":"Car Park","input_type":"select","score":1},{"id":"q5","number":5,"text":"Family Toilets","input_type":"select","score":1}]}]},"questions_answer_json":[{"id":"q1","correct_answer":"A","acceptable_answers":["A"],"score":1,"explanation":"The first aid point is located in the south-west corner, just past the corner when you head left from the Main Entrance. This matches label A on the map.","transcript_evidence":"If you head left along the south-west path, you will find our first aid point just past the corner."},{"id":"q2","correct_answer":"B","acceptable_answers":["B"],"score":1,"explanation":"The club shop is at the south-east corner, reached by heading right from the Main Entrance. This matches label B on the map.","transcript_evidence":"On the opposite side of the entrance — so heading right from the Main Entrance towards the south-east corner — you will come across our club shop. It is right at that south-east corner."},{"id":"q3","correct_answer":"C","acceptable_answers":["C"],"score":1,"explanation":"The refreshment kiosk is on the west side of the stadium, approximately halfway along the path. This matches label C on the map.","transcript_evidence":"If you continue further and walk along the west side of the stadium, you will find a refreshment kiosk about halfway up that path."},{"id":"q4","correct_answer":"E","acceptable_answers":["E"],"score":1,"explanation":"The car park is on the north side of the stadium, positioned to the east of centre. This matches label E on the map.","transcript_evidence":"For those arriving by car, the car park is on the north side of the stadium, to the east of centre."},{"id":"q5","correct_answer":"F","acceptable_answers":["F"],"score":1,"explanation":"The family toilets are on the east side of the stadium, roughly halfway along that path. This matches label F on the map.","transcript_evidence":"The family toilets are situated on the east side, roughly halfway along that path."}],"thumbnail":null,"map_image":null,"type":"map_labelling","topic":null,"tests_taken":"0","level":"B1","audio_file":[]}	{"status":"published"}	\N	\N
