ea08e7e0-f0b6-45c4-b020-14ceb3f7aaea	College Map - Facilities	college-map-facilities	A map labelling listening practice about locations inside a college	british	\N	0	t	\N	\N	\N	2026-05-30 12:19:13.663154+00	2026-05-30 12:19:13.663154+00	published	{"source_type":"uploaded_audio_and_map","map_labels":["A","B","C","D","E","F","G","H","I","J","K"],"task_format":"Write the correct letter, A-K, next to Questions 1-3.","estimated_level_reason":"Basic map labelling with only 3 questions and clear letter options.","needs_review":true}	{"groups":[{"id":"g1","type":"map_labelling","title":"Questions 1-3","instruction":"Write the correct letter, A-K, next to Questions 1-3.","question_range":{"from":1,"to":3},"media":{"type":"image","field":"image_file"},"options":{"type":"letters","values":["A","B","C","D","E","F","G","H","I","J","K"]},"questions":[{"id":"q1","number":1,"text":"Administration office","input_type":"select"},{"id":"q2","number":2,"text":"Café","input_type":"select"},{"id":"q3","number":3,"text":"Student common room","input_type":"select"}]}]}	{"answers":[{"question_id":"q1","correct_answer":null,"acceptable_answers":[],"explanation":"","transcript_evidence":""},{"question_id":"q2","correct_answer":null,"acceptable_answers":[],"explanation":"","transcript_evidence":""},{"question_id":"q3","correct_answer":null,"acceptable_answers":[],"explanation":"","transcript_evidence":""}]}	\N	0efdda83-9884-423c-9e1b-eb17d5be8f57	map_labelling	\N	0	basic
ac2babeb-afbd-499a-9cac-10238c31e1b7	Village Facilities Map	village-facilities-map	A map labelling listening practice about facilities in a village.	british	188	5	f	Label the map below. Write the correct letter, A-H, next to Questions 1-5.	Welcome to everyone here. I hope you enjoy your stay in our village and enjoy the local scenery. I’ll tell you a bit about the forest and mountain tracks in a minute, but first, I’ll just give you an idea of where everything is in the village. So, we’re here in the tourist information centre, and when you come out of the centre, you're on Willow Lane, just opposite the pond. If you want to get to the supermarket for your supplies of food and water, go right, that's the quickest way, and then turn right at the top of Willow Lane, and it's the second building you come to opposite the old railway station. If you're planning on doing some serious climbing and you need some equipment, we do have an excellent climbing supplies store just five minutes' walk away. Turn left once you're outside the tourist information centre, take Willow Lane all the way up to Pine Street - you want to go left along here - then keep walking and go past Mountain Road on your right, until you come to the next turning on the left - head down there, and you'll come to the climbing supplies store. If you get to the small building that sells ski passes, you'll know you've gone too far. You also need to head to Pine Street for the museum - it's small but well worth a visit if you're interested in the history of the village and the old gold mining industry. So, when you reach Pine Street from here, you'll see the old railway line on the other side of the road - turn left into Pine Street, and keep going until you come to Mountain Road, and just up here, the museum will be on your left, just behind the railway line. Don't worry about crossing over the tracks. The trains stopped running through here in 1985. If you're planning on following one of the easier forest walks, you might like to hire a bicycle. To get to the hire shop, again you need to head to Pine Street. On the left-hand side of Pine Street, you'll see the Town Hall, go down the little road that you come to just before it, and you'll find the bike hire shop just behind the hall. They have a good range of bikes so I'm sure you'll find something that suits your needs. Last but not least, if you're hungry after a long day's trek I can recommend our local café. Again, when you leave the tourist information centre, turn right and follow Willow Lane until it joins Pine Street - and right opposite - on the far side of the railway tracks - is the café.	\N	2026-05-31 06:48:30.51049+00	2026-05-31 06:48:30.51049+00	published	{"source_type":"uploaded_audio_and_map","visual_type":"village_map","map_listening_category":"map","task_format":"Label the map below. Write the correct letter, A-H, next to Questions 1-5.","answer_key":{"1":"G","2":"D","3":"A","4":"E","5":"C"},"map_labels":["A","B","C","D","E","F","G","H"],"needs_review":true,"audio_duration_seconds_detected":188}	{"groups":[{"id":"g1","type":"map_labelling","title":"Questions 1-5","instruction":"Label the map below. Write the correct letter, A-H, next to Questions 1-5.","question_range":{"from":1,"to":5},"media":{"type":"image","field":"image_file"},"options":{"type":"letters","values":["A","B","C","D","E","F","G","H"]},"questions":[{"id":"q1","number":1,"text":"Supermarket","input_type":"select"},{"id":"q2","number":2,"text":"Climbing supplies store","input_type":"select"},{"id":"q3","number":3,"text":"Museum","input_type":"select"},{"id":"q4","number":4,"text":"Bike hire shop","input_type":"select"},{"id":"q5","number":5,"text":"Café","input_type":"select"}]}]}	{"answers":[{"question_id":"q1","correct_answer":"G","acceptable_answers":["G"],"explanation":"The supermarket is reached by going right from the tourist information centre, then right at the top of Willow Lane. It is the second building opposite the old railway station, which is G.","transcript_evidence":"Go right, that's the quickest way, and then turn right at the top of Willow Lane, and it's the second building you come to opposite the old railway station."},{"question_id":"q2","correct_answer":"D","acceptable_answers":["D"],"explanation":"The climbing supplies store is reached by going left along Pine Street, past Mountain Road, then taking the next turning on the left. It is before the ski passes building, which places it at D.","transcript_evidence":"Keep walking and go past Mountain Road on your right, until you come to the next turning on the left - head down there, and you'll come to the climbing supplies store. If you get to the small building that sells ski passes, you'll know you've gone too far."},{"question_id":"q3","correct_answer":"A","acceptable_answers":["A"],"explanation":"The museum is on Pine Street near Mountain Road, on the left, just behind the railway line. This matches A.","transcript_evidence":"Turn left into Pine Street, and keep going until you come to Mountain Road, and just up here, the museum will be on your left, just behind the railway line."},{"question_id":"q4","correct_answer":"E","acceptable_answers":["E"],"explanation":"The bike hire shop is behind the Town Hall, reached by going down the small road just before it. This location is E.","transcript_evidence":"On the left-hand side of Pine Street, you'll see the Town Hall, go down the little road that you come to just before it, and you'll find the bike hire shop just behind the hall."},{"question_id":"q5","correct_answer":"C","acceptable_answers":["C"],"explanation":"The café is opposite Willow Lane on the far side of the railway tracks. This matches C.","transcript_evidence":"When you leave the tourist information centre, turn right and follow Willow Lane until it joins Pine Street - and right opposite - on the far side of the railway tracks - is the café."}]}	\N	b5e32d61-4078-49d6-aee8-36cc133cdb2a	map_labelling	\N	0	basic
0ea3b60c-f6b9-4e6a-b34a-d3dc018a983c	Biogas Plant Diagram	biogas-plant-diagram	A diagram labelling listening practice about the parts of a biogas plant.	british	120	7	t	Label the diagram. Write the correct word or phrase for each label, A-G.	\N	\N	2026-05-31 06:51:24.107844+00	2026-05-31 06:51:24.107844+00	published	{"source_type":"uploaded_audio_and_diagram","visual_type":"biogas_plant_diagram","map_listening_category":"diagram","task_format":"Label the diagram. Write the correct word or phrase for each label, A-G.","diagram_labels":["A","B","C","D","E","F","G"],"needs_review":true,"audio_duration_seconds_detected":120}	{"groups":[{"id":"g1","type":"diagram_labelling","title":"Questions A-G","instruction":"Label the diagram. Write the correct word or phrase for each label, A-G.","question_range":{"from":"A","to":"G"},"answer_rule":{"max_words":3,"allow_number":false,"case_sensitive":false},"media":{"type":"image","field":"image_file"},"questions":[{"id":"qA","number":"A","text":"Label A","input_type":"text"},{"id":"qB","number":"B","text":"Label B","input_type":"text"},{"id":"qC","number":"C","text":"Label C","input_type":"text"},{"id":"qD","number":"D","text":"Label D","input_type":"text"},{"id":"qE","number":"E","text":"Label E","input_type":"text"},{"id":"qF","number":"F","text":"Label F","input_type":"text"},{"id":"qG","number":"G","text":"Label G","input_type":"text"}]}]}	{"answers":[{"question_id":"qA","correct_answer":null,"acceptable_answers":[],"explanation":"","transcript_evidence":""},{"question_id":"qB","correct_answer":null,"acceptable_answers":[],"explanation":"","transcript_evidence":""},{"question_id":"qC","correct_answer":null,"acceptable_answers":[],"explanation":"","transcript_evidence":""},{"question_id":"qD","correct_answer":null,"acceptable_answers":[],"explanation":"","transcript_evidence":""},{"question_id":"qE","correct_answer":null,"acceptable_answers":[],"explanation":"","transcript_evidence":""},{"question_id":"qF","correct_answer":null,"acceptable_answers":[],"explanation":"","transcript_evidence":""},{"question_id":"qG","correct_answer":null,"acceptable_answers":[],"explanation":"","transcript_evidence":""}]}	\N	a21e33c3-e4db-486a-81eb-2ef096714726	diagram_labelling	\N	0	basic
cf29994c-9181-4ed1-924f-f7bfb259202e	Organic Farm Layout	organic-farm-layout	An outdoor map of an Organic Farm featuring a central pond, paths, and various locations.	British English	\N	5	t	Label the map below. Write the correct letter, A-F, next to Questions 1-5.	Welcome to our organic farm. I'm delighted to show you around today. We're currently standing at the Main Entrance. If you look straight ahead, you'll see a path leading to the central pond in the middle of the farm. First, on your left, just past the entrance, is our Farm Shop. You can buy fresh produce and honey here at the end of your visit. Opposite that, on the right side of the path, is a building, but that is actually the tool shed, which is only for staff, so please do not enter. As you continue up the path, walk past the central pond. On your left, just past the pond, you will find the Herb Garden, where we grow culinary and medicinal herbs. Across the path from the Herb Garden, directly opposite it, is the Tomato Greenhouse, where we cultivate organic tomatoes. Further along, at the top-right corner of the farm, past the greenhouse, you'll find the Beehives. Our bees are essential for pollinating the crops. Finally, if you head to the far north-west corner, just beyond the Herb Garden, you'll reach the Compost Area, where we recycle all our organic waste. Enjoy your tour!	\N	2026-06-17 01:13:47.596518+00	2026-06-17 01:13:47.596518+00	published	{"schema_version":"visual_labelling_listening_v1","topic":"Organic Farm","speaker_role":"Farm Guide","image_generation_prompt":"A clean, simplified 2D map plan of an Organic Farm for a language exam. At the bottom centre, there is a clear text label reading 'Main Entrance'. In the absolute centre of the map is a small circular water feature labelled 'Central Pond'. A straight grey path connects the entrance to the pond, and branches go north, east, and west. There are six neutral, identical rectangular plots, each clearly marked with a single bold capital letter from A to F. Plot A is on the left side of the entrance path. Plot B is on the right side of the entrance path. Plot C is near the top-left, just past the pond. Plot D is to the right (east) of the pond. Plot E is at the top-right corner. Plot F is at the far north-west corner. The entire map is set against a white background, completely free of icons, trees, beehives, compost bins, greenhouses, tools, or decorative elements.","difficulty_notes":{"word_count":193,"visible_label_count":6,"question_count":5,"distractor_label_count":1,"why_this_level":"Contains standard B1 spatial language like 'past', 'opposite', 'directly opposite', 'beyond', 'far corner', and 'top-right corner'. Word count is 193 words, which is within the 180-260 word range. Features 1 distractor label (B, the tool shed).","distractors":["The tool shed (label B) near the entrance which is only for staff."],"key_phrases":["just past","opposite","past the pond","directly opposite","beyond"],"visual_fairness_check":{"can_learners_guess_answers_from_image_alone":false,"anti_leak_checked":true,"notes":"Every letter label corresponds to a completely featureless, identical plot. There are no signs, icons, or visual clues to guess which label is the greenhouse, herb garden, farm shop, beehives, or compost area."}}}	{"groups":[{"id":"g1","type":"map_labelling","title":"Questions 1-5","instruction":"Label the map below. Write the correct letter, A-F, next to Questions 1-5.","question_range":{"from":1,"to":5},"media":{"image":{"type":"image","field":"image_file"},"audio":{"type":"audio","field":"audio_file"}},"options":{"type":"letters","values":["A","B","C","D","E","F"]},"questions":[{"id":"q1","number":1,"text":"Farm Shop","input_type":"select","score":1},{"id":"q2","number":2,"text":"Herb Garden","input_type":"select","score":1},{"id":"q3","number":3,"text":"Tomato Greenhouse","input_type":"select","score":1},{"id":"q4","number":4,"text":"Beehives","input_type":"select","score":1},{"id":"q5","number":5,"text":"Compost Area","input_type":"select","score":1}]}]}	[{"id":"q1","correct_answer":"A","acceptable_answers":["A"],"score":1,"explanation":"The Farm Shop is located just past the entrance on the left-hand side, which corresponds to label A.","transcript_evidence":"First, on your left, just past the entrance, is our Farm Shop."},{"id":"q2","correct_answer":"C","acceptable_answers":["C"],"score":1,"explanation":"The Herb Garden is located just past the pond on the left-hand side, which corresponds to label C.","transcript_evidence":"On your left, just past the pond, you will find the Herb Garden"},{"id":"q3","correct_answer":"D","acceptable_answers":["D"],"score":1,"explanation":"The Tomato Greenhouse is directly opposite the Herb Garden on the other side of the path, which corresponds to label D.","transcript_evidence":"Across the path from the Herb Garden, directly opposite it, is the Tomato Greenhouse"},{"id":"q4","correct_answer":"E","acceptable_answers":["E"],"score":1,"explanation":"The Beehives are located at the top-right corner of the farm, past the greenhouse, which corresponds to label E.","transcript_evidence":"Further along, at the top-right corner of the farm, past the greenhouse, you'll find the Beehives."},{"id":"q5","correct_answer":"F","acceptable_answers":["F"],"score":1,"explanation":"The Compost Area is located in the far north-west corner, just beyond the Herb Garden, which corresponds to label F.","transcript_evidence":"Finally, if you head to the far north-west corner, just beyond the Herb Garden, you'll reach the Compost Area"}]	\N	48fdba1c-e953-4834-8fca-39e69d92176b	map_labelling	\N	7	medium
bd11f758-8a3e-4ccb-854d-6dfa2c7df8fb	Welcome to the Riverside Food Festival	welcome-to-the-riverside-food-festival	An outdoor map of the Riverside Food Festival grounds, featuring entrance gates, paths, a central Piazza, a Main Stage, and various food and drink stall locations.	British English	\N	7	t	Label the map below. Write the correct letter, A-J, next to Questions 1-7.	Hello everyone, and a very warm welcome to the Annual Riverside Food Festival! I’m Sarah, your event director, and I’m delighted to guide you through our layout this year. We’ve expanded the festival grounds quite a bit, so please look at your maps while I explain where everything is. Right now, we are gathered at the main Entrance, located at the very bottom center of your map. Immediately to your left, just past the gates, you’ll see the Information Booth, where you can grab event guides and schedules. Let’s start with our first highlight: the Craft Beer Pavilion. If you look at the bottom-left corner of the map, just past the Information Booth and right along the western perimeter wall, you'll spot that pavilion. It features local microbreweries. Just next to the Information Booth, you'll notice a small ticket booth. We no longer use this since tickets are digital, so feel free to bypass it. Now, if we walk up the Main Path towards the center, we reach the Central Piazza, which has seating. Just before you get to the Piazza, on the left-hand side of the Main Path, is the Artisan Cheese Stall. It was originally going to be placed on the opposite side of the path, but we decided this spot near the shade of the large oak trees was much better. Continuing past the Piazza, straight ahead at the very top of the map, you’ll see the Main Stage, where live chef demonstrations will take place all day. If you go to the far North, directly behind the Main Stage, you’ll find the VIP Dining Area. This area is reserved for pass-holders and sponsors. To the left of the Main Stage, tucked into the far top-left corner of the site, is the International Food Court. You'll find cuisines from five different continents there. Now, let’s look at the eastern side of the festival site. If you walk from the entrance along the path heading east, or to your right, the first building you'll see in the bottom-right corner is the First Aid Post. We had originally set up the Volunteer Rest Zone there, but for safety reasons, we swapped them, so the first aid team is now right there, and the volunteer rest zone has been moved to the quieter spot directly behind it. Moving further north along that eastern path, about halfway up, is the Gourmet Dessert Stand, which is famous for its artisanal ice creams. Finally, if you keep going all the way to the top-right corner, next to the waste recycling area, you'll find the Vegetarian Kitchen, serving a fantastic selection of plant-based street food. Have a wonderful day tasting everything, and enjoy the festival!	\N	2026-06-18 10:40:11.158511+00	2026-06-18 10:40:11.158511+00	published	{"schema_version":"visual_labelling_listening_v1","topic":"Food Festival Site","speaker_role":"Event Director","image_generation_prompt":"A clean, minimalist 2D outdoor map layout of a Food Festival Site on a white background. At the bottom centre, there is a clear label 'Entrance' leading into a Main Path. To the left of the path, just inside, is a stall labelled 'Information Booth'. In the middle of the layout is a central square labelled 'Central Piazza'. At the top centre is a stage labelled 'Main Stage'. There are ten neutral, outline rectangles representing stall locations, each labelled with a bold capital letter from A to J. Plot C is in the bottom-left corner. Plot J is adjacent to the Information Booth. Plot B is on the left of the Main Path just before the Piazza. Plot I is on the right of the Main Path, opposite B. Plot A is in the top-left corner. Plot G is at the very top, behind the Main Stage. Plot D is in the bottom-right corner. Plot H is directly behind D. Plot E is halfway up the path on the right side of the map. Plot F is in the top-right corner. No icons of food, beer glasses, stages, or first aid crosses are present on the image.","difficulty_notes":{"word_count":429,"visible_label_count":10,"question_count":7,"distractor_label_count":3,"why_this_level":"Designed for C1 listening difficulty: natural spoken style with complex spatial references, old/new configuration changes ('originally set up... but swapped them'), negations and unused structures ('no longer use this'), and dense directional guidance.","distractors":["Volunteer Rest Zone (H) which was swapped with the First Aid Post location.","Cookery Workshop (I) which was the original planned location for the Cheese Stall.","Ticket Booth (J) which is adjacent to the Information Booth but is no longer in use."],"key_phrases":["western perimeter wall","no longer use this","just before you get to","originally going to be placed","directly behind","swapped them","halfway up"],"visual_fairness_check":{"can_learners_guess_answers_from_image_alone":false,"anti_leak_checked":true,"notes":"All stall locations are completely neutral rectangles labelled A-J without icons, names, or graphic hints."}}}	{"groups":[{"id":"g1","type":"map_labelling","title":"Questions 1-7","instruction":"Label the map below. Write the correct letter, A-J, next to Questions 1-7.","question_range":{"from":1,"to":7},"media":{"image":{"type":"image","field":"image_file"},"audio":{"type":"audio","field":"audio_file"}},"options":{"type":"letters","values":["A","B","C","D","E","F","G","H","I","J"]},"questions":[{"id":"q1","number":1,"text":"Craft Beer Pavilion","input_type":"select","score":1},{"id":"q2","number":2,"text":"Artisan Cheese Stall","input_type":"select","score":1},{"id":"q3","number":3,"text":"VIP Dining Area","input_type":"select","score":1},{"id":"q4","number":4,"text":"International Food Court","input_type":"select","score":1},{"id":"q5","number":5,"text":"First Aid Post","input_type":"select","score":1},{"id":"q6","number":6,"text":"Gourmet Dessert Stand","input_type":"select","score":1},{"id":"q7","number":7,"text":"Vegetarian Kitchen","input_type":"select","score":1}]}]}	[{"id":"q1","correct_answer":"C","acceptable_answers":["C"],"score":1,"explanation":"The Craft Beer Pavilion is located in the bottom-left corner of the map, just past the Information Booth along the western wall, marked as label C.","transcript_evidence":"If you look at the bottom-left corner of the map, just past the Information Booth and right along the western perimeter wall, you'll spot that pavilion."},{"id":"q2","correct_answer":"B","acceptable_answers":["B"],"score":1,"explanation":"The Artisan Cheese Stall is located on the left-hand side of the Main Path, just before the Central Piazza, marked as label B.","transcript_evidence":"Just before you get to the Piazza, on the left-hand side of the Main Path, is the Artisan Cheese Stall."},{"id":"q3","correct_answer":"G","acceptable_answers":["G"],"score":1,"explanation":"The VIP Dining Area is located at the far top boundary, directly behind the Main Stage, marked as label G.","transcript_evidence":"If you go to the far North, directly behind the Main Stage, you’ll find the VIP Dining Area."},{"id":"q4","correct_answer":"A","acceptable_answers":["A"],"score":1,"explanation":"The International Food Court is tucked into the far top-left corner of the site, marked as label A.","transcript_evidence":"To the left of the Main Stage, tucked into the far top-left corner of the site, is the International Food Court."},{"id":"q5","correct_answer":"D","acceptable_answers":["D"],"score":1,"explanation":"The First Aid Post is located in the bottom-right corner of the map, having swapped locations with the Volunteer Rest Zone, marked as label D.","transcript_evidence":"the first building you'll see in the bottom-right corner is the First Aid Post."},{"id":"q6","correct_answer":"E","acceptable_answers":["E"],"score":1,"explanation":"The Gourmet Dessert Stand is located about halfway up the eastern path, marked as label E.","transcript_evidence":"Moving further north along that eastern path, about halfway up, is the Gourmet Dessert Stand"},{"id":"q7","correct_answer":"F","acceptable_answers":["F"],"score":1,"explanation":"The Vegetarian Kitchen is located in the top-right corner of the map, next to the recycling area, marked as label F.","transcript_evidence":"Finally, if you keep going all the way to the top-right corner, next to the waste recycling area, you'll find the Vegetarian Kitchen"}]	\N	66d4ddf8-a70e-4d56-ab92-aac6d696ff67	map_labelling	\N	0	C1
5aaa34d2-c34c-4c63-ba02-057f722e791f	Using a Coffee Machine	using-a-coffee-machine	A cross-section or external diagram of a home coffee machine.	British	\N	4	t	Label the diagram below. Write the correct letter, A-D, next to Questions 1-4.	Hello and welcome to your new coffee machine. Let me explain how to use it. First, look at the back of the machine. At the top, on the right side, you will find the water tank. Fill this with cold water. Next, look at the top left of the machine. This is the coffee bean hopper. Pour your fresh beans in here. Then, the machine will grind them for you. Now, in the centre, behind the main door, is the brewing chamber. This is where the hot water mixes with the coffee. You need to clean this part every week. Finally, look at the base of the machine, underneath the cups. This is the drip tray. It catches any spilled coffee, so remember to empty it regularly. Enjoy your coffee!	\N	2026-06-11 14:14:23.105993+00	2026-06-11 14:14:23.105993+00	published	{"schema_version":"visual_labelling_listening_v1","topic":"Coffee Machine","speaker_role":"Instructor","image_generation_prompt":"A clean, simple technical line drawing of a home coffee machine on a white background. The drawing shows the main door in the centre and some cups resting at the bottom centre. There are four neutral, unlabelled shapes or areas pointed to by clear letter labels A, B, C, and D. Label A points to a container on the top left. Label B points to an internal area in the centre, behind the main door. Label C points to a tall container on the back right. Label D points to a shallow tray area at the base, underneath the cups. Do not print correct answer names on the image. Do not reveal answer locations through icons, coffee beans, water drops, or semantic visual clues. Question-target locations must be visually neutral.","difficulty_notes":{"word_count":131,"visible_label_count":4,"question_count":4,"distractor_label_count":0,"why_this_level":"Meets A2 criteria: ~130 words, 4 questions, 4 labels (A-D), 0 distractors, simple location directions.","distractors":[],"key_phrases":["at the back","at the top","on the right side","top left","in the centre","behind","at the base","underneath"],"visual_fairness_check":{"can_learners_guess_answers_from_image_alone":false,"anti_leak_checked":true,"notes":"No visual clues are given for the tank, hopper, chamber, or tray, only simple shapes and letter labels."}}}	{"groups":[{"id":"g1","type":"diagram_labelling","title":"Questions 1-4","instruction":"Label the diagram below. Write the correct letter, A-D, next to Questions 1-4.","question_range":{"from":1,"to":4},"media":{"image":{"type":"image","field":"image_file"},"audio":{"type":"audio","field":"audio_file"}},"options":{"type":"letters","values":["A","B","C","D"]},"questions":[{"id":"q1","number":1,"text":"Water tank","input_type":"text","score":1},{"id":"q2","number":2,"text":"Coffee bean hopper","input_type":"text","score":1},{"id":"q3","number":3,"text":"Brewing chamber","input_type":"text","score":1},{"id":"q4","number":4,"text":"Drip tray","input_type":"text","score":1}]}]}	[{"id":"q1","correct_answer":"C","acceptable_answers":["C","c"],"score":1,"explanation":"The water tank is located at the back of the machine, at the top on the right side.","transcript_evidence":"First, look at the back of the machine. At the top, on the right side, you will find the water tank."},{"id":"q2","correct_answer":"A","acceptable_answers":["A","a"],"score":1,"explanation":"The coffee bean hopper is located at the top left of the machine.","transcript_evidence":"Next, look at the top left of the machine. This is the coffee bean hopper."},{"id":"q3","correct_answer":"B","acceptable_answers":["B","b"],"score":1,"explanation":"The brewing chamber is in the centre, behind the main door.","transcript_evidence":"Now, in the centre, behind the main door, is the brewing chamber."},{"id":"q4","correct_answer":"D","acceptable_answers":["D","d"],"score":1,"explanation":"The drip tray is located at the base of the machine, underneath the cups.","transcript_evidence":"Finally, look at the base of the machine, underneath the cups. This is the drip tray."}]	\N	ee4e7440-3d4e-449b-89c5-5a8be31c20f0	diagram_labelling	\N	1	basic
d3307137-ae3c-4387-a33a-30b8d6a440d9	Lakeside Park Facilities	lakeside-park-facilities	An outdoor map of Lakeside Park featuring a central lake, entrances, paths, and various facilities.	British English	\N	6	t	Label the map below. Write the correct letter, A-H, next to Questions 1-6.	Welcome everyone to Lakeside Park. I'm the head ranger, and I'd like to give you a quick overview of the park's layout so you can make the most of your visit today. You are all currently standing at the Main Entrance, looking into the park. Straight ahead of you, before you reach the lake, is a large building. This is the Visitor Centre. You can get detailed maps and information here. Now, many of you have asked about getting some food and drink. We used to have a small cafe just to the right of the Main Entrance, but that building is no longer open to the public; it's just for staff parking now. Instead, to find the new Cafe, you need to walk along the path that goes around the eastern side of the central lake. Keep walking right to the far side of the lake, and you'll find it near the North Gate. There's a building just beyond the cafe in the top corner, but don't go there as that's just a maintenance shed. If you are interested in renting out a rowing boat, the Boat Hire is also on the eastern side of the lake. Walk up the main east path, and it's right next to the water. Directly opposite the Boat Hire, on the other side of the east path, you'll see a beautiful area enclosed by hedges. This is the Rose Garden, which is currently in full bloom. Over on the western side of the park, there's plenty to do as well. As you walk up the west path from the Main Entrance, before you reach the Old Bridge, you'll see a large fenced-off area. This is the Children's Playground, which we recently expanded. Continuing further on the west path, you'll walk over the Old Bridge. Just past the bridge, on the left-hand side, is a lovely shaded spot. This is the Picnic Area, perfect for relaxing after a walk. We hope you have a wonderful day exploring Lakeside Park!	\N	2026-06-10 14:42:52.557501+00	2026-06-10 14:42:52.557501+00	published	{"schema_version":"visual_labelling_listening_v1","topic":"Lakeside Park","speaker_role":"Park Guide","visual_blueprint":{"visual_type":"map_labelling","description":"An outdoor map of Lakeside Park featuring a central lake, entrances, paths, and various facilities.","canvas_layout":"The Main Entrance is at the bottom centre. A path leads straight ahead towards the central lake. Paths diverge to go around the east and west sides of the lake. There is an Old Bridge on the west path. The North Gate is at the top centre.","fixed_orientation_landmarks":[{"name":"Main Entrance","position":"Bottom centre","visible_text_on_image":"Main Entrance","why_safe_to_show":"Starting point for orientation."},{"name":"Central Lake","position":"Middle of the map","visible_text_on_image":"Central Lake","why_safe_to_show":"Major geographical feature used for relative spatial directions."},{"name":"North Gate","position":"Top centre","visible_text_on_image":"North Gate","why_safe_to_show":"Orientation point at the top of the map."},{"name":"The Old Bridge","position":"On the west path crossing a small stream","visible_text_on_image":"Old Bridge","why_safe_to_show":"Reference point for navigation on the west path."}],"visible_labels":[{"label":"A","position":"Just to the right of the Main Entrance","is_answer_label":false,"hidden_correct_place_or_part":"Staff Parking (former cafe)","visual_appearance":"neutral shape only","visual_neutrality_rule":"Do not reveal this answer or distractor through icons, objects, signs, products, tools, furniture, symbols, vehicles, or semantic visual clues."},{"label":"B","position":"Straight ahead from the Main Entrance, just before the Central Lake","is_answer_label":true,"hidden_correct_place_or_part":"Visitor Centre","visual_appearance":"neutral shape only","visual_neutrality_rule":"Do not reveal this answer or distractor through icons, objects, signs, products, tools, furniture, symbols, vehicles, or semantic visual clues."},{"label":"C","position":"On the west path, just past the Old Bridge","is_answer_label":true,"hidden_correct_place_or_part":"Picnic Area","visual_appearance":"neutral shape only","visual_neutrality_rule":"Do not reveal this answer or distractor through icons, objects, signs, products, tools, furniture, symbols, vehicles, or semantic visual clues."},{"label":"D","position":"On the east path, right next to the water of the Central Lake","is_answer_label":true,"hidden_correct_place_or_part":"Boat Hire","visual_appearance":"neutral shape only","visual_neutrality_rule":"Do not reveal this answer or distractor through icons, objects, signs, products, tools, furniture, symbols, vehicles, or semantic visual clues."},{"label":"E","position":"On the far side of the lake, near the North Gate","is_answer_label":true,"hidden_correct_place_or_part":"Cafe","visual_appearance":"neutral shape only","visual_neutrality_rule":"Do not reveal this answer or distractor through icons, objects, signs, products, tools, furniture, symbols, vehicles, or semantic visual clues."},{"label":"F","position":"In the top right corner, just beyond label E","is_answer_label":false,"hidden_correct_place_or_part":"Maintenance Shed","visual_appearance":"neutral shape only","visual_neutrality_rule":"Do not reveal this answer or distractor through icons, objects, signs, products, tools, furniture, symbols, vehicles, or semantic visual clues."},{"label":"G","position":"On the west path, before reaching the Old Bridge","is_answer_label":true,"hidden_correct_place_or_part":"Children's Playground","visual_appearance":"neutral shape only","visual_neutrality_rule":"Do not reveal this answer or distractor through icons, objects, signs, products, tools, furniture, symbols, vehicles, or semantic visual clues."},{"label":"H","position":"On the east path, directly opposite label D, away from the water","is_answe